INSERT INTO `Question_backup` VALUES ('00f18242-aad9-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','A: Is that Sue’s printer? B: Yes, it’s _______ printer.','[\"she\", \"his\", \"her\", \"hers\"]','her','\"Her\" zamirinden sonra isim geldiğinde kullanılır (her printer = onun yazıcısı).',1,'cce5cff5-717d-4a4c-9d72-d554baa5e779'),('00f1a614-aad9-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','A: _______ Sarah and Megan real estate agents? B: No, they _______.','[\"Are / are\", \"Is / aren’t\", \"Is / isn’t\", \"Are / aren’t\"]','Are / aren’t','Çoğul özne (Sarah and Megan) ile soru sorarken “Are” kullanılır, olumsuzu “aren’t” olur.',1,'cce5cff5-717d-4a4c-9d72-d554baa5e779'),('00f1a90c-aad9-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','_______ Mary and Tom _______ at a drugstore?','[\"Are / work\", \"Does / works\", \"Is / work\", \"Do / work\"]','Do / work','Mary ve Tom çoğul öznedir, bu yüzden “Do” yardımcı fiili kullanılır.',1,'cce5cff5-717d-4a4c-9d72-d554baa5e779'),('00f1accc-aad9-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','_______ he _______ every day?','[\"Is / swim\", \"Is / swims\", \"Does / swim\", \"Does / swims\"]','Does / swim','He/she/it özneleriyle “Does” kullanılır, fiil yalın halde kalır (swim).',1,'cce5cff5-717d-4a4c-9d72-d554baa5e779'),('00f1aeac-aad9-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','A: Where _______ you yesterday? B: I _______ at school.','[\"did / was\", \"were / was\", \"were / were\", \"was / was\"]','were / was','“You” için geçmiş zaman “were”, “I” için “was” kullanılır.',1,'cce5cff5-717d-4a4c-9d72-d554baa5e779'),('00f1b5dc-aad9-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','A: What _______ you _______ at university? B: Medicine.','[\"were / study\", \"were / studied\", \"did / study\", \"did / studied\"]','did / study','Geçmiş zamanda soru “did” ile yapılır, fiil yalın halde kalır (study).',1,'cce5cff5-717d-4a4c-9d72-d554baa5e779'),('00f1b816-aad9-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','Paris is _______ interesting city. There are a lot of places to visit in _______ city.','[\"an / the\", \"a / the\", \"an / an\", \"the / a\"]','an / the','Sesli harfle başlayan kelimelerden önce “an” gelir, belirli bir şehirden bahsederken “the” kullanılır.',1,'cce5cff5-717d-4a4c-9d72-d554baa5e779'),('00f1bab4-aad9-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','Jane usually _______ to work, but today she _______ the bus.','[\"is driving / is taking\", \"drive / is taking\", \"drives / takes\", \"drives / is taking\"]','drives / is taking','“Usually” (genellikle) alışkanlık belirtir → present simple. “Today” şu anı belirtir → present continuous.',1,'cce5cff5-717d-4a4c-9d72-d554baa5e779'),('00f1c018-aad9-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','I _______ help you now. I don’t have any time. I’m so busy.','[\"don’t\", \"‘m not\", \"can’t\", \"aren’t\"]','can’t','“Can’t” bir şeyi yapamam anlamında kullanılır (yetersizlik).',1,'cce5cff5-717d-4a4c-9d72-d554baa5e779'),('01624064-8c47-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','I _____ the laundry when I heard a loud noise.','[\"did\",\"was doing\",\"have done\",\"do\"]','was doing','\"Geçmişte devam eden: I was doing the laundry.\"',4,'ce5b9917-2879-46ac-9f01-25fe11cc9376'),('01626db4-8c47-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','I _____ Amy an hour ago. She _____ to her roommate.','[\"saw/was talking\",\"have seen/was talking\",\"saw/had talked\",\"have seen/is talking\"]','saw/was talking','\"Past simple + past continuous: I saw ... she was talking.\"',4,'ce5b9917-2879-46ac-9f01-25fe11cc9376'),('0162719c-8c47-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','Sarah promised _____ help me with my homework after school.','[\"helping\",\"help\",\"to help\",\"helped\"]','to help','\"Promise + to V: promised to help.\"',4,'ce5b9917-2879-46ac-9f01-25fe11cc9376'),('01627610-8c47-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','John was very tired yesterday because he _____ up late the night before to finish his project.','[\"had stayed/woke\",\"has stayed/had woken\",\"stayed/had woken\",\"has stayed/woken\"]','had stayed/woke','\"Past perfect + past simple: had stayed ... woke.\"',4,'ce5b9917-2879-46ac-9f01-25fe11cc9376'),('016349f0-8c47-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','Emma was nervous... she realized she _____ her resume at home.','[\"forgot\",\"has forgotten\",\"had forgotten\",\"forgotten\"]','had forgotten','\"Past perfect: she had forgotten.\"',4,'ce5b9917-2879-46ac-9f01-25fe11cc9376'),('01634e50-8c47-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','Mark has lived in Paris _____ he was born.','[\"for\",\"since\",\"ever\",\"until\"]','since','\"Since + starting point: since he was born.\"',4,'ce5b9917-2879-46ac-9f01-25fe11cc9376'),('02e83fcc-8bdb-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','Your mother and your father are your _____.','[\"parents\",\"uncles\",\"cousins\",\"children\"]','parents','\"Anne ve baba = parents (ebeveynler).\"',2,'24c604e2-b224-4335-9c8a-02ad2dcc28b3'),('02e88df6-8bdb-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','______ names are Tony and Mary.','[\"We\",\"Us\",\"Our\",\"Ours\"]','Our','\"İsimler onların → Our names (bizim isimlerimiz).\"',2,'24c604e2-b224-4335-9c8a-02ad2dcc28b3'),('02e892b0-8bdb-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','He always eats dinner ______ two o’clock.','[\"in\",\"at\",\"on\",\"before\"]','at','\"Saatlerle at kullanılır: at two o’clock.\"',2,'24c604e2-b224-4335-9c8a-02ad2dcc28b3'),('02e896ac-8bdb-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','My mother works in a school. ____ school is very big.','[\"The\",\"-\",\"A\",\"An\"]','The','\"Okul belli olduğu için The kullanılır.\"',2,'24c604e2-b224-4335-9c8a-02ad2dcc28b3'),('02e89a80-8bdb-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','______ do homework every day?','[\"You have to\",\"Do you have to\",\"Do you have\",\"Have you got\"]','Do you have to','\"Zorunluluk sorusu: Do you have to do homework?\"',2,'24c604e2-b224-4335-9c8a-02ad2dcc28b3'),('02e89f44-8bdb-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','My brother loves Jane but she doesn’t love ______.','[\"his\",\"he\",\"her\",\"him\"]','him','\"Jane erkek kardeşini sevmiyor → love him.\"',2,'24c604e2-b224-4335-9c8a-02ad2dcc28b3'),('02e8b9d4-8bdb-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','______ a car? ---- No, I can’t.','[\"Can you drive\",\"You can drive\",\"Drive\",\"You drive\"]','Can you drive','\"Ehliyet sorusu: Can you drive a car?\"',2,'24c604e2-b224-4335-9c8a-02ad2dcc28b3'),('02e8be5c-8bdb-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','She can’t ______ a computer.','[\"using\",\"to use\",\"use\",\"used\"]','use','\"Can + fiilin yalın hali: can’t use.\"',2,'24c604e2-b224-4335-9c8a-02ad2dcc28b3'),('02e8c154-8bdb-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','______ flowers in your garden?','[\"There are some\",\"Are there any\",\"are any\",\"Is there any\"]','Are there any','\"Soru: Are there any flowers…?\"',2,'24c604e2-b224-4335-9c8a-02ad2dcc28b3'),('02e8c5aa-8bdb-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','There _____ books in the living room.','[\"aresome\",\"issome\",\"are any\",\"is a\"]','are some','\"Çokluk olduğu için are some kullanılır.\"',2,'24c604e2-b224-4335-9c8a-02ad2dcc28b3'),('02e8c938-8bdb-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','There is a picture ______ the window and the door.','[\"under\",\"below\",\"between\",\"before\"]','between','\"İki nesnenin arasında: between.\"',2,'24c604e2-b224-4335-9c8a-02ad2dcc28b3'),('02e8d8a6-8bdb-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','Where were you ______ night?','[\"last\",\"yesterday\",\"ago\",\"before\"]','last','\"Zaman ifadesi: last night.\"',2,'24c604e2-b224-4335-9c8a-02ad2dcc28b3'),('02e8dbbc-8bdb-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','Where did he ____ last summer?','[\"goes\",\"went\",\"go\",\"going\"]','go','\"Did + fiilin yalın hali: did he go.\"',2,'24c604e2-b224-4335-9c8a-02ad2dcc28b3'),('02e8df0e-8bdb-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','I don’t know ______ here.','[\"somebody\",\"nobody\",\"nothing\",\"anybody\"]','anybody','\"Olumsuzda anybody kullanılır.\"',2,'24c604e2-b224-4335-9c8a-02ad2dcc28b3'),('02e8e288-8bdb-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','Why ______ you at school yesterday?','[\"aren’t\",\"weren’t\",\"isn’t\",\"wasn’t\"]','weren’t','\"Geçmiş zaman sorusu: Why weren’t you...?\"',2,'24c604e2-b224-4335-9c8a-02ad2dcc28b3'),('0f92799e-abbc-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','That’s the scientist __________ discovered a new species last year, and her work has inspired many young researchers.','[\"which\", \"who\", \"whose\", \"where\"]','who','“Who” insanlardan bahsederken kullanılır → “the scientist who discovered…”.',3,'0de5fd2d-555f-4ba1-bccb-450b8df2f817'),('0f92ed66-abbc-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','It was __________ an exciting match that the crowd cheered more loudly than ever before.','[\"very\", \"such\", \"so\", \"too\"]','such','“Such + noun” yapısı → “such an exciting match”. “So” sıfatla kullanılır, isimle değil.',3,'0de5fd2d-555f-4ba1-bccb-450b8df2f817'),('0f92f40a-abbc-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','I’ll send you an email as soon as I ______ (get) home, so you ______ (have) all the details before the meeting, which starts at 3 p.m.','[\"will get / are having\", \"got / have had\", \"get / will have\", \"am getting / would have\"]','get / will have','Zaman yan cümlelerinde “will” kullanılmaz → “as soon as I get”. Ana cümlede “will have”.',3,'0de5fd2d-555f-4ba1-bccb-450b8df2f817'),('0f930666-abbc-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','She ______ (fly) to New York next month for a business conference, and she ______ (already book) her flight and hotel.','[\"was going to fly / already booked\", \"will fly / have already booked\", \"flies / had already booked\", \"is flying / has already booked\"]','is flying / has already booked','“Next month” → gelecek planı, “is flying”. “Has already booked” → present perfect, sonucu var.',3,'0de5fd2d-555f-4ba1-bccb-450b8df2f817'),('0f930c56-abbc-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','I won’t go on holiday ____ I save enough money, which might take a few more months.','[\"unless\", \"before\", \"after\", \"as soon as\"]','unless','“Unless” = “if not” yani “...olmazsa”. → “I won’t go unless I save money.”',3,'0de5fd2d-555f-4ba1-bccb-450b8df2f817'),('0f9310fc-abbc-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','By the time you arrive at the airport, I ______ (finish) all the check-in procedures.','[\"will finish\", \"will be finishing\", \"will have finished\", \"will be finished\"]','will have finished','“By the time” → belirli zamana kadar tamamlanmış eylem → future perfect tense.',3,'0de5fd2d-555f-4ba1-bccb-450b8df2f817'),('0f93155c-abbc-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','The company, ________ employees are highly skilled, is expanding rapidly.','[\"which\", \"whose\", \"that\", \"where\"]','whose','“Whose” = sahiplik bildirir. → “The company whose employees…”',3,'0de5fd2d-555f-4ba1-bccb-450b8df2f817'),('0f932aa6-abbc-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','If I ________ (be) more careful while driving, I ________ (not crash) my car last night.','[\"am / wouldn’t have crashed\", \"had been / wouldn’t crash\", \"was / wouldn’t crash\", \"had been / wouldn’t have crashed\"]','had been / wouldn’t have crashed','Geçmişteki pişmanlık → 3. tip koşul → “had been / wouldn’t have crashed”.',3,'0de5fd2d-555f-4ba1-bccb-450b8df2f817'),('0f93a3dc-abbc-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','If I ________ (be) you, I would take the job offer, as it would be a great opportunity for my career.','[\"am\", \"were\", \"was\", \"would\"]','were','“If I were you” sabit kalıptır. Tavsiye verirken kullanılır.',3,'0de5fd2d-555f-4ba1-bccb-450b8df2f817'),('0f93a60c-abbc-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','They ________ (prepare) for the upcoming presentation for weeks, and now they are confident about their performance.','[\"have prepared\", \"had prepared\", \"have been preparing\", \"were preparing\"]','have been preparing','“Have been preparing” → süregelen geçmişten bugüne kadar devam eden eylem (present perfect continuous).',3,'0de5fd2d-555f-4ba1-bccb-450b8df2f817'),('10b4eff2-7bc7-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','Thank you for letting me know about this birthday wish of _________.','[\"him\",\"me\",\"your\",\"his\"]','his','Doğru cevap \"his\" çünkü iyelik zamiri gerekiyor.',4,'ce5b9917-2879-46ac-9f01-25fe11cc9376'),('10b5dd2c-7bc7-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','She _________ strictly since Christmas and so far she _________ eight kilos.','[\"was dieting/loses\",\"dieted/loses\",\"has been dieting/has lost\",\"is dieting/lost\"]','has been dieting/has lost','Present Perfect Continuous + Present Perfect kullanılır.',4,'ce5b9917-2879-46ac-9f01-25fe11cc9376'),('10b5fbea-7bc7-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','As the president _________ the hall, all the guests _________ to their feet to welcome him.','[\"was entering/has risen\",\"entered/rose\",\"is entering/rise\",\"has entered/were rising\"]','entered/rose','Geçmişte gerçekleşen iki olay için Simple Past kullanılır.',4,'ce5b9917-2879-46ac-9f01-25fe11cc9376'),('10b61864-7bc7-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','In parts of Africa, women still _________ water a long way to their village.','[\"used to carry\",\"might carry\",\"have to carry\",\"must have carried\"]','have to carry','\"have to\" zorunluluk anlamı verir, bağlama en uygun olanıdır.',3,'cf4e6d96-0c6c-4a7d-8576-c7f376611f51'),('10b6338a-7bc7-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','Would you mind _________ your cigarette smoke in my face? It’s getting on my nerves.','[\"not blowing\",\"not to blow\",\"not blow\",\"didn’t blow\"]','not blowing','Would you mind + V-ing yapısı kullanılır.',3,'cf4e6d96-0c6c-4a7d-8576-c7f376611f51'),('10b64cb2-7bc7-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','My aunt, _________ son-in law is the managing director of a large company, has been to a garden party at Buckingham Palace.','[\"whose\",\"which\",\"whom\",\"who\"]','whose','\"whose\" iyelik bildiren bağlaçtır.',4,'ce5b9917-2879-46ac-9f01-25fe11cc9376'),('10b66800-7bc7-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','We sometimes spend a week in a cottage in Wales _________ belongs to a friend of mine.','[\"where\",\"whose\",\"that\",\"how\"]','that','Doğru cevap \"that\" çünkü \"cottage\"i tanımlıyor.',3,'cf4e6d96-0c6c-4a7d-8576-c7f376611f51'),('10b67e26-7bc7-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','_________ being an accomplished artist, Leonardo da Vinci was also a sculptor, an architect and a man of science.','[\"In order to\",\"However\",\"Not only\",\"Besides\"]','Besides','Doğru cevap \"Besides\" ek bilgi vermek için kullanılır.',4,'ce5b9917-2879-46ac-9f01-25fe11cc9376'),('10b6b6d4-7bc7-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','His parents were happy that he managed to gain a university degree _________ his handicap.','[\"thus\",\"despite\",\"though\",\"provided\"]','despite','\"despite\" zıtlık ifade eder.',3,'cf4e6d96-0c6c-4a7d-8576-c7f376611f51'),('10b6d498-7bc7-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','Spiders _________ by many people, but most of them _________ to be harmless.','[\"had feared/were known\",\"are feared/are known\",\"have been feared/knew\",\"will be feared/know\"]','are feared/are known','Passive voice present tense doğru kullanımdır.',4,'ce5b9917-2879-46ac-9f01-25fe11cc9376'),('10b6ebc2-7bc7-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','If he _________ in the woods at that particular time, he _________ the suicide.','[\"wouldn’t be/hadn’t witnessed\",\"weren’t/hasn’t been witnessing\",\"wasn’t/ought not to witnessed\",\"hadn’t been/wouldn’t have witnessed\"]','hadn’t been/wouldn’t have witnessed','3rd Conditional yapısı: If + Past Perfect → would have V3.',4,'ce5b9917-2879-46ac-9f01-25fe11cc9376'),('10b6ff4a-7bc7-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','Owing to the disagreements between the two banks, the meeting was ______________ until further notice.','[\"made up\",\"put off\",\"looked after\",\"thrown away\"]','put off','\"put off\" ertelemek anlamına gelir.',3,'cf4e6d96-0c6c-4a7d-8576-c7f376611f51'),('10b711d8-7bc7-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','Although local people speak a different language, English is the ______________ language of law and education in many countries.','[\"official\",\"native\",\"mother\",\"informal\"]','official','\"official language\" doğru collocation’dır.',3,'cf4e6d96-0c6c-4a7d-8576-c7f376611f51'),('10b72254-7bc7-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','Susie lent Jim her book, and ____________ he let her borrow his computer game.','[\"on average\",\"at least\",\"in return\",\"for instance\"]','in return','Doğru cevap \"in return\", karşılık olarak anlamına gelir.',2,'19707430-e702-42b6-b923-9ffbd079495d'),('10b734e2-7bc7-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','The doctor advised his patient to ______________ another expert if he required a second opinion.','[\"consult\",\"introduce\",\"test\",\"examine\"]','consult','\"consult another expert\" doğru kullanımdır.',3,'cf4e6d96-0c6c-4a7d-8576-c7f376611f51'),('10b74a90-7bc7-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','The public decided to ____________ the police in their hunt for the criminal.','[\"attach\",\"join\",\"connect\",\"add\"]','join','\"join the police\" doğru kullanımdır.',2,'19707430-e702-42b6-b923-9ffbd079495d'),('10b75daa-7bc7-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','Oh no, I can’t face the thought of today’s maths lesson - one hour of total ____________!','[\"education\",\"intellect\",\"presence\",\"boredom\"]','boredom','\"total boredom\" doğru ifadedir.',2,'19707430-e702-42b6-b923-9ffbd079495d'),('122d8cfc-9573-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','Many customers absolutely ---- no idea that their chocolate bar was made from materials ---- by a maltreated child slave.','[\"have / gathered\",\"had / were gathered\",\"may have / are gathered\",\"have had / gathering\",\"were having / being gathered\"]','had / were gathered','Cümle geçmiş zamanda kurulmuş ve edilgen yapı (were gathered) gerekiyor. Doğru cevap B seçeneğidir.',3,'d475b5bf-9c5e-4b8f-a462-40a9e5132dd1'),('122dd400-9573-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','She ______ in the company for five years before she decided to leave.','[\"works\",\"is working\",\"has worked\",\"had worked\",\"was working\"]','had worked','Bir olaydan önce gerçekleşmiş eylem olduğu için past perfect (had worked) kullanılır.',3,'d475b5bf-9c5e-4b8f-a462-40a9e5132dd1'),('122de4fe-9573-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','The book ______ by the time you return it.','[\"is damaged\",\"was damaged\",\"has been damaged\",\"will have been damaged\",\"had damaged\"]','will have been damaged','Gelecekte bir zamana kadar tamamlanmış olacak pasif bir eylem için future perfect passive (will have been damaged) kullanılır.',3,'d475b5bf-9c5e-4b8f-a462-40a9e5132dd1'),('1f6e46b0-ac73-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','With his great style, Messi quickly became a world-famous football star. Today, football fans all around the world ____________ that he is the present-day Maradona.','[\"think\", \"are thinking\", \"has been thinking\", \"thought\"]','think','\"All around the world\" genel bir durumu belirtir; bu yüzden simple present tense (think) doğru seçenektir.',4,'0aa198f6-0667-40af-8eb6-7006549511b7'),('1f6e6d20-ac73-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','Because there was a huge rainstorm, the flight ___________ for more than an hour. The airport was full of angry passengers.','[\"delayed\", \"is delayed\", \"delays\", \"was delayed\"]','was delayed','Geçmişte tamamlanmış bir olayı anlatır; bu yüzden past simple (was delayed) doğru cevaptır.',4,'0aa198f6-0667-40af-8eb6-7006549511b7'),('1f6e6f64-ac73-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','Since the Industrial Revolution of the 19th century, human activities ____________ the Earth’s ecological balance significantly.','[\"has damaged\", \"have been damaging\", \"damaged\", \"are being damaging\"]','have been damaging','\"Since\" ifadesi geçmişten bugüne süregelen bir durumu anlatır; present perfect continuous (have been damaging) doğru seçenektir.',4,'0aa198f6-0667-40af-8eb6-7006549511b7'),('1f6e7356-ac73-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','I am taking Spanish classes at the community college because I _________________ in Barcelona next spring and I thought knowing a little Spanish would make me feel more comfortable.','[\"am going to study\", \"have been studying\", \"will study\", \"have studied\"]','am going to study','\"Next spring\" geleceğe yöneliktir; planlı bir eylem olduğu için \'am going to study\' doğru seçenektir.',4,'0aa198f6-0667-40af-8eb6-7006549511b7'),('1f6e74f0-ac73-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','Before the legislation made last year, smoking ____________________ in closed areas in the whole country.','[\"is allowed\", \"did allowed\", \"was allowed\", \"had allowed\"]','was allowed','Geçmişte geçerli olan bir durum anlatılır; past simple passive (was allowed) doğru seçenektir.',4,'0aa198f6-0667-40af-8eb6-7006549511b7'),('1f6e7acc-ac73-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','Recently, a survey was carried out in order to determine the good and the bad drivers: Young, old, male and female. Which ones are ________________ of all?','[\"the safer\", \"safest\", \"the most safest\", \"the safest\"]','the safest','Superlative yapılarda “the + adjective + est” kullanılır; “the safest” doğrudur.',4,'0aa198f6-0667-40af-8eb6-7006549511b7'),('1f6e7eaa-ac73-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','Children are exposed to many advertisements for unhealthy foods, ______________ parents must educate their children about good food and nutrition.','[\"because\", \"therefore\", \"since\", \"whereas\"]','therefore','İlk cümle neden, ikinci cümle sonuç bildiriyor; bu nedenle bağlaç “therefore” doğru seçenektir.',4,'0aa198f6-0667-40af-8eb6-7006549511b7'),('1f6e8274-ac73-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','A: Do you know where Pedro is? I have been calling his office for almost an hour, but no answer. Isn’t he working today? B: You know he only skips work for important events, and today is the final game of the World Cup. He ____________________ at a bar watching the game.','[\"must be\", \"should be\", \"might be\", \"can be\"]','must be','Yüksek olasılık ifade edilir; bu durumda “must be” en uygun seçenektir.',4,'0aa198f6-0667-40af-8eb6-7006549511b7'),('1f6e8634-ac73-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','The teacher wanted to know ________________________.','[\"why students hadn’t done their assignment on Geography\", \"how could students prevent themselves from wasting time\", \"whether did students understand the topic of reported questions in English\", \"what is the best method to write an effective essay\"]','why students hadn’t done their assignment on Geography','“Wanted to know” ifadesinden sonra dolaylı soru gelir; bu yüzden “why students hadn’t done …” doğru yapıdır.',4,'0aa198f6-0667-40af-8eb6-7006549511b7'),('1f6e8b20-ac73-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','Anne continued knocking the door hard _____________ she knew quite well that this was the only way to wake her husband up.','[\"although\", \"while\", \"because\", \"but\"]','because','“Only way” ifadesi nedeni belirtir; bu yüzden “because” doğru seçenektir.',4,'0aa198f6-0667-40af-8eb6-7006549511b7'),('21c6e776-8e98-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','It is now well-known that all that annoying endless buffering happens because of your internet service provider which is doing that on purpose.','[\"Bütün bu sonu gelmeyen, sinir bozucu tamponlama internet servis sağlayıcınız tarafından yapılıyor.\",\"İnternet servis sağlayıcınız sonu gelmeyen, sinir bozucu tamponlamaları kasıtlı olarak yapmıştı.\",\"Sonu gelmeyen tamponlamalar herkesin sinirini bozmaktadır ve internet servis sağlayıcınız bunu kasıtlı olarak yapıyor.\",\"Bütün bu sinir bozucu sonsuz tamponlamanın, bunu bilerek yapan internet servis sağlayıcınız nedeniyle gerçekleştiği artık bilinmektedir.\",\"Bütün bu sonu gelmeyen, sinir bozucu tamponlamanın nedenini öğrenmek isterseniz internet servis sağlayıcınızla iletişime geçin.\"]','Bütün bu sinir bozucu sonsuz tamponlamanın, bunu bilerek yapan internet servis sağlayıcınız nedeniyle gerçekleştiği artık bilinmektedir.','\"It is now well-known that ... happens because of ... → artık bilinmektedir ki ... nedeniyle gerçekleşmektedir.\"',3,'d475b5bf-9c5e-4b8f-a462-40a9e5132dd1'),('23f80b06-8d85-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','There are innovative and flexible pathways in distance learning or e-learning courses, ________.','[\"they require four months’ full-time study, while diplomas require nine months’ full study\",\n   \"that are particularly recommended for students planning to pursue doctoral studies\",\n   \"which may allow for the completion of a master’s degree in up to five years\",\n   \"when students are able to relate the sciences taught online to everyday scenarios\"]','which may allow for the completion of a master’s degree in up to five years','\"Doğru bağlaç: ‘which may allow...’. Uzak eğitimde esneklik vurgulanıyor.\"',3,'cf4e6d96-0c6c-4a7d-8576-c7f376611f51'),('23f881d0-8d85-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','We wouldn’t have started the International food project ________.','[\"as long as the chef had agreed to get involved in it\",\n   \"if academics from all the university departments came\",\n   \"after institutions reached out to a much wider audience\",\n   \"unless the public engagement unit had funded it\"]','unless the public engagement unit had funded it','\"Üçüncü tip koşul: wouldn’t have + V3 ... unless ... had V3.\"',3,'cf4e6d96-0c6c-4a7d-8576-c7f376611f51'),('23f91b86-8d85-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','________ by the time they announce their company has gone bankrupt.','[\"It faced opposition from a number of stakeholders\",\n   \"Having over a thousand workers means a lot of expenses\",\n   \"The banks are not able to write off the company’s debts\",\n   \"The employees will have been made redundant\"]','The employees will have been made redundant','\"Gelecek tamamlanmış zaman: will have been made redundant by the time...\"',3,'cf4e6d96-0c6c-4a7d-8576-c7f376611f51'),('23f91e7e-8d85-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','________, governments have been unprepared for spikes in water demand.','[\"As populations have increased in size and relocated to urban areas\",\n   \"Due to the fact that people are managing water resources carefully\",\n   \"Since the reasons for our worldwide water problems are numerous\",\n   \"Because millions of people will feel the effects of water shortages\"]','As populations have increased in size and relocated to urban areas','\"Doğru neden-sonuç ilişkisi: Nüfus artışı ve şehirleşme → su talebi artar.\"',3,'cf4e6d96-0c6c-4a7d-8576-c7f376611f51'),('2b895bc6-8e3a-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','Paulina’s classmate invited her out for dinner after class, but she politely _____ since she had other plans.','[\"expanded\",\"released\",\"spared\",\"declined\"]','declined','\"Polite refusal → she declined (nazikçe reddetti).\"',4,'e6eec0bb-827c-4a91-b0fb-540f12289300'),('2b8a59d6-8e3a-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','We _______ unexpected results in our latest experiment.','[\"selected\",\"conducted\",\"retrieved\",\"obtained\"]','obtained','\"Sonuçları elde etmek → obtained results (doğru kullanım).\"',4,'e6eec0bb-827c-4a91-b0fb-540f12289300'),('2b8a5d8c-8e3a-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','Even though many different languages are spoken in the United States, the _______ language is English.','[\"factual\",\"superficial\",\"predominant\",\"monumental\"]','predominant','\"Baskın/dominant dil → predominant language.\"',4,'e6eec0bb-827c-4a91-b0fb-540f12289300'),('2b8a5f4e-8e3a-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','Scientists are carrying out serious studies so as to find solutions to _________ diseases.','[\"inadequate\",\"ineffective\",\"incurable\",\"invasive\"]','incurable','\"Çözüm aranan hastalıklar → incurable diseases (tedavi edilemez hastalıklar).\"',4,'e6eec0bb-827c-4a91-b0fb-540f12289300'),('2b8a6174-8e3a-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','Cats are supposed to be very clean animals and keep themselves and their _________ free of dirt.','[\"demonstration\",\"surroundings\",\"corporations\",\"refugees\"]','surroundings','\"Kediler kendilerini ve çevresini temiz tutar → surroundings.\"',4,'e6eec0bb-827c-4a91-b0fb-540f12289300'),('2b8a63b8-8e3a-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','Some historians think that the first true golfers were ancient shepherds who passed the time ____ using their wooden staffs to knock small stones ____ holes.','[\"in / to\",\"by / into\",\"by / over\",\"for / under\"]','by / into','\"Passed the time by doing sth ... knock stones into holes.\"',4,'e6eec0bb-827c-4a91-b0fb-540f12289300'),('2b8ac592-8e3a-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','Philosophers have debated the relation _____ thought and emotions _____ at least two millennia.','[\"form / over\",\"between / for\",\"in / by\",\"through / to\"]','between / for','\"The relation between A and B ... for two millennia (süre belirten).\"',4,'e6eec0bb-827c-4a91-b0fb-540f12289300'),('31e101fa-aacc-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','A: You look really angry. ___________? B: I lent some money to Jason in March and he hasn’t paid it back yet.','[\"Are you excited\", \"Are you interesting\", \"What happened\", \"When do you see the doctor\"]','What happened','Use \"What happened?\" to ask the reason for someone being angry or upset.',4,'0c559ccd-2f8e-4644-b642-2f0cac112047'),('31e12702-aacc-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','A: This t-shirt is large. I think I need a smaller one. B: Ok, _____________ A: Small.','[\"What size are you?\", \"Which color do you prefer?\", \"Do you like wearing t-shirt?\", \"You are not slim enough.\"]','What size are you?','Asking about size is the correct response when someone mentions clothing fit.',4,'0c559ccd-2f8e-4644-b642-2f0cac112047'),('31e12a40-aacc-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','A: We bought this mobile phone last month from your shop but I want to give it back. B: Oh, _____________? We can try to fix it if you like.','[\"Why did you choose it?\", \"Is something wrong with it?\", \"Is it expensive for you?\", \"Why didn’t you like it?\"]','Is something wrong with it?','The appropriate response when a customer wants to return a product is to ask if there is a problem.',4,'0c559ccd-2f8e-4644-b642-2f0cac112047'),('31e12c66-aacc-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','A: Timothy. _______with these suitcases? They are really heavy. I can’t carry them by myself. B: Surely. I’m coming now.','[\"Can you give me a hand\", \"Did you see me\", \"Would you like a hand\", \"Why don’t you call\"]','Can you give me a hand','\"Can you give me a hand?\" is the common phrase to ask for help physically.',4,'0c559ccd-2f8e-4644-b642-2f0cac112047'),('31e12ef0-aacc-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','A: Do you want me to clean the windows for you? You look really tired. B: __________of you. I started cleaning the house yesterday and doing housework since then. I have no more energy.','[\"I am very happy\", \"It is rude\", \"You are very nice\", \"It is really kind\"]','It is really kind','\"It is really kind of you\" is the polite response to someone offering help or noticing effort.',4,'0c559ccd-2f8e-4644-b642-2f0cac112047'),('31e13198-aacc-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','A: Hello, Are you busy? B: Hi there. No, it’s OK. Come on in. _____________, please. You must be tired.','[\"It is nice to see you\", \"Take a seat\", \"It is a nice surprise\", \"You look great\"]','Take a seat','When inviting someone indoors, \"Take a seat\" is appropriate.',4,'0c559ccd-2f8e-4644-b642-2f0cac112047'),('31e133d2-aacc-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','A: Simon , it is cold and rainy today. You cannot go swimming. B: _____________ Yesterday, it was hot and sunny. Today, it is cold and rainy.','[\"Help yourself!\", \"That sounds terrific!\", \"Just my luck!\", \"Congratulations!\"]','Just my luck!','Use \"Just my luck!\" to express disappointment at bad timing or circumstances.',4,'0c559ccd-2f8e-4644-b642-2f0cac112047'),('31e13602-aacc-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','A: Hi, Bill! You look sorry. ___________ B: I have just learned that I failed in Math and Chemistry exams so I won’t be able to graduate this year.','[\"What is the matter?\", \"Who passed the exam?\", \"When did you start studying Math?\", \"Why don’t you study harder?\"]','What is the matter?','Use \"What is the matter?\" to ask about a problem or situation causing concern.',4,'0c559ccd-2f8e-4644-b642-2f0cac112047'),('31e138fa-aacc-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','A: Hi, Nancy. “Jennifer Lopez” is going to have a concert in Istanbul next month. B: _____________. I am planning to go to that concert with my boyfriend.','[\"I heard about that\", \"I don’t like watching animation films\", \"I am sorry\", \"That’s terrible\"]','I heard about that','\"I heard about that\" shows awareness of information and is a natural conversational response.',4,'0c559ccd-2f8e-4644-b642-2f0cac112047'),('31e145e8-aacc-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','A: Alfred, I finally passed the driving test, so I can get my driving license. B: ____________ You can buy a car now.','[\"Congratulations!\", \"I am sorry to hear that.\", \"Help yourself.\", \"That is bad.\"]','Congratulations!','Use \"Congratulations!\" to celebrate someone’s achievement.',4,'0c559ccd-2f8e-4644-b642-2f0cac112047'),('407f5d1a-ac70-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','---- who began his career in Antalya as a teacher.','[\"The job is too demanding for a girl\", \"You should consult the others\", \"My brother is now a famous writer\", \"It\'s not easy to be a working mother\", \"Merve is another top businesswoman\"]','My brother is now a famous writer','Cümle bir özne ister; “My brother is now a famous writer” anlam ve yapı olarak uygundur.',4,'08aa5752-09aa-45f6-972b-3d893074caa6'),('4081e350-ac70-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','Because Muş and Bitlis are geographically very close to each other, ----.','[\"they can’t easily trade with each other\", \"they are different from each other in many ways\", \"their economies showed a fast growing\", \"they are both very developed\", \"transportation between them is very easy\"]','transportation between them is very easy','\"Because\" neden-sonuç ilişkisi kurar; yakın oldukları için ulaşım kolaydır.',4,'08aa5752-09aa-45f6-972b-3d893074caa6'),('40898934-ac70-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','---- when she retires next year.','[\"Many changes took place\", \"The meeting has been put off\", \"Her daughter will be the manager\", \"I didn’t say anything at the party\", \"I was able to send you the price list\"]','Her daughter will be the manager','Emekli olunca kızının yönetici olacağı gelecek zamana uygun doğru seçenektir.',4,'08aa5752-09aa-45f6-972b-3d893074caa6'),('408ca10a-ac70-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','---- because it helps us to express the words correctly.','[\"A dictionary is usually a reliable guide to pronunciation\", \"Examinations given during the term are useful\", \"The composition teacher realized\", \"I understood the importance of speaking and writing effectively\", \"None of them was adequately prepared\"]','A dictionary is usually a reliable guide to pronunciation','Cümle “because” ile açıklama gerektiriyor; sözlük doğru telaffuzu gösterir.',4,'08aa5752-09aa-45f6-972b-3d893074caa6'),('408cb91a-ac70-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','Kenya, a country famous for its safaris and coffee, is situated on the east coast of Africa.','[\"Safarileri ve kahvesiyle bilinen ve bir Afrika ülkesi olan Kenya, kıtanın doğu kıyısında yer alır.\", \"Afrika’nın doğu kıyısında yer alan Kenya, hem safarileri hem de kahvesiyle ünlü bir ülkedir.\", \"Safarileri ve kahvesiyle ünlü bir ülke olan Kenya, Afrika’nın doğu kıyısında yer alır.\", \"Kenya, safarileri ve kahvesiyle tanınan bir ülke olarak Afrika’nın doğu kıyısında bulunmaktadır.\", \"Afrika’nın doğu kıyısında bulunan Kenya, safarileri ve kahvesiyle ünlü bir ülke olarak bilinmektedir.\"]','Safarileri ve kahvesiyle ünlü bir ülke olan Kenya, Afrika’nın doğu kıyısında yer alır.','Tam çeviri akıcı ve doğru anlam verir: “Safarileri ve kahvesiyle ünlü bir ülke olan Kenya...”',4,'08aa5752-09aa-45f6-972b-3d893074caa6'),('408cea5c-ac70-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','We value all the arts because they enrich and diversify our emotional life.','[\"Duygu yaşamımızın zengin olmasını sağlayan tüm sanatlar bizim için değerlidir.\", \"Tüm sanatlara değer vererek duygu yaşamımızın zengin ve çeşitli olmasını sağlarız.\", \"Duygu yaşamımızın zenginleşmesi ve farklı olması için tüm sanatlara değer veririz.\", \"Tüm sanatlara değer veririz çünkü duygu yaşamımızı zenginleştirir ve çeşitlendirirler.\", \"Bizim için değerli olan tüm sanatlar, duygu yaşamımızı zenginleştirir ve çeşitlendirir.\"]','Tüm sanatlara değer veririz çünkü duygu yaşamımızı zenginleştirir ve çeşitlendirirler.','\"Because\" → neden belirtiyor; doğru anlamlı çeviri bu seçenekte.',4,'08aa5752-09aa-45f6-972b-3d893074caa6'),('408cecbe-ac70-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','Cutting down trees to build houses not only damages the environment, but also threatens human health.','[\"Ev yapmak amacıyla ağaçları kesmek sadece çevreye zarar vermekle kalmaz, aynı zamanda insan sağlığını da tehdit eder.\", \"Ev yaparken bazı ağaçların kesilmesi çevreye zarar verir ve insan sağlığını tehdit eder.\", \"Ev yapmak amacıyla ağaçların kesilmesi insan sağlığını tehdit etmese de çevreye zarar verir.\", \"Ağaçların ev yapmak için kesilmesi hem çevreyi hem de insan sağlığını kötü etkiler.\", \"Çevreye zarar veren ve insan sağlığını tehdit eden nedenlerden biri ağaçların ev yapmak için kesilmesidir.\"]','Ev yapmak amacıyla ağaçları kesmek sadece çevreye zarar vermekle kalmaz, aynı zamanda insan sağlığını da tehdit eder.','\"Not only... but also\" → iki olumsuz sonucu birleştirir; doğru çeviri bu seçenekte.',4,'08aa5752-09aa-45f6-972b-3d893074caa6'),('408cedae-ac70-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','The development of computers has been amazingly rapid, and the future may be different from today’s forecasts.','[\"Bilgisayarlarda gelişimin şaşırtıcı derecede hızlı olması, geleceğin öngörülenden farklı olabileceğini gösteriyor.\", \"Bilgisayarlar şaşırtıcı derecede hızlı bir gelişim gösterdiği için gelecek bugünden farklı olabilir.\", \"Bilgisayarların gelişimi şaşırtıcı derecede hızlı olmuştur ve gelecek, bugünün tahminlerinden farklı olabilir.\", \"Şaşırtıcı derecede hızlı bir gelişim gösteren bilgisayarlar ile gelecek, bugünden farklı olabilir.\", \"Bilgisayarlar şaşırtıcı derecede hızlı bir gelişim göstermiştir, fakat gelecek, bugün düşünülenlerden farklı olabilir.\"]','Bilgisayarların gelişimi şaşırtıcı derecede hızlı olmuştur ve gelecek, bugünün tahminlerinden farklı olabilir.','İki cümle birleştiriliyor: geçmişteki hızlı gelişim + geleceğe dair tahmin farkı.',4,'08aa5752-09aa-45f6-972b-3d893074caa6'),('408cee9e-ac70-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','Olimpiyat Oyunları, başlangıçta bir gün süren çeşitli spor etkinliklerinden oluşuyordu, ancak günümüzde haftalarca süren dünya çapında bir spor olayı olmuştur.','[\"Although the Olympic Games were initially different sporting activities which lasted for one day, today they have turned into a worldwide sports event and take several weeks.\", \"At the beginning, the Olympic Games consisted of various sporting activities, lasting for one day, but in our time, they have become a worldwide sports event, lasting for weeks.\", \"Originally, the Olympic Games took place on one day and included different kinds of sports, but today they have developed into a major sports event in the world, lasting for many weeks.\", \"Once the Olympic Games lasted only for one day and consisted of many different sporting activities, but today they have become one of the major sports events in the world, which last several weeks.\", \"Today the Olympic Games are a major sports event in the world, and last many weeks, even though at the beginning they were only a one-day sports event.\"]','Originally, the Olympic Games took place on one day and included different kinds of sports, but today they have developed into a major sports event in the world, lasting for many weeks.','“Originally” → başlangıçta; geçmiş ve günümüz farkını net anlatır.',4,'08aa5752-09aa-45f6-972b-3d893074caa6'),('408d34ee-ac70-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','Dedem yetmişine gelince, kendini çok yaşlı hissetti ve çocukları ile torunlarını son kez görmek için veda ziyaretleri yapmaya başladı.','[\"Once my grandfather was seventy, he realized he was very old, so made some farewell visits to his children and grandchildren.\", \"When my grandfather got to be seventy, he felt very old, and began to make farewell visits to see his children and grandchildren for the last time.\", \"My grandfather, when he was seventy, wanted to see his children and grandchildren for, probably, the last time, and so made some farewell visits.\", \"When my grandfather was seventy years old, he went on farewell visits to his children and grandchildren, and so saw them for the last time.\", \"My grandfather really felt very old when he was seventy, so he made a last visit to all his children and his grandchildren.\"]','When my grandfather got to be seventy, he felt very old, and began to make farewell visits to see his children and grandchildren for the last time.','“Got to be seventy” → yetmişine gelince; “began to make farewell visits” doğru anlamı verir.',4,'08aa5752-09aa-45f6-972b-3d893074caa6'),('4756318c-8b2c-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','We planned to have a three-week holiday but we had to come back a week earlier when we ran ........ of money.','[\"over\",\"out\",\"into\",\"after\"]','out','\"Run out of\" means to finish all of something, here it refers to money.',3,'0c5f6d1d-1a1a-4879-8e5e-71efa44d5b40'),('47565c2a-8b2c-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','I don’t like George at all; he is one of those ........ people who think that they are more important than others.','[\"sensitive\",\"arrogant\",\"stubborn\",\"decisive\"]','arrogant','\"Arrogant\" describes people who think they are more important than others.',3,'0c5f6d1d-1a1a-4879-8e5e-71efa44d5b40'),('47565ee6-8b2c-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','Fred didn’t want to re-marry; he never ........ the shock of losing his wife.','[\"got over\",\"came by\",\"took of\",\"looked after\"]','got over','\"Get over\" means to recover from something, here from the shock of losing his wife.',3,'0c5f6d1d-1a1a-4879-8e5e-71efa44d5b40'),('47566170-8b2c-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','The boys were ........ when they came in from football, so I directly sent them to have a bath.','[\"lousy\",\"noisy\",\"filthy\",\"bossy\"]','filthy','\"Filthy\" means very dirty, so it fits the context after playing football.',3,'0c5f6d1d-1a1a-4879-8e5e-71efa44d5b40'),('4756654e-8b2c-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','If you want to spend your winter holiday on the Alps, you should ........ a hotel room now because it’s very crowded there in the winter season.','[\"book\",\"examine\",\"reveal\",\"decorate\"]','book','\"Book\" means to reserve in advance, which makes sense for a hotel room.',3,'0c5f6d1d-1a1a-4879-8e5e-71efa44d5b40'),('47566f12-8b2c-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','The animals which have been kept in ........ for a long time would probably not stay alive if they were set free in the wild today.','[\"danger\",\"chance\",\"search\",\"captivity\"]','captivity','\"Captivity\" means kept in cages or controlled environments, the correct answer here.',3,'0c5f6d1d-1a1a-4879-8e5e-71efa44d5b40'),('47c4c572-abc3-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','To get dressed means to ……………','[\"buy new clothes\", \"put clothes on\", \"clean your clothes\", \"take clothes off\"]','put clothes on','\"To get dressed\" → kıyafet giymek demektir, yani \"put clothes on\".',2,'05e48369-5ea9-4ef0-ab6f-9f5d29358929'),('47c516f8-abc3-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','If someone wants privacy, he or she wants to ……………','[\"talk with others\", \"be left alone\", \"have lots of friends\", \"be helped by others\"]','be left alone','\"Privacy\" gizlilik demektir → yalnız bırakılmak istenir.',2,'05e48369-5ea9-4ef0-ab6f-9f5d29358929'),('47c5193c-abc3-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','To protect something means to keep it ……………','[\"quiet\", \"happy\", \"safe\", \"clean\"]','safe','\"To protect\" → bir şeyi korumak, güvenli tutmak demektir.',2,'05e48369-5ea9-4ef0-ab6f-9f5d29358929'),('47c53480-abc3-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','A person who grew up in a city ……………','[\"had children in that city\", \"moved there after school\", \"lived there as a child\", \"visited the city as a child\"]','lived there as a child','\"Grew up\" → çocukluğunu geçirdi → \"lived there as a child\".',2,'05e48369-5ea9-4ef0-ab6f-9f5d29358929'),('47c536b0-abc3-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','Mary: \"I will eat steak for dinner.\" Jill: \"Mary said (that) she......................eat steak for dinner.\"','[\"might\", \"will\", \"would\", \"will not\"]','would','Dolaylı anlatımda \"will\" → \"would\" olur.',2,'05e48369-5ea9-4ef0-ab6f-9f5d29358929'),('47c53840-abc3-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','Four houses in Dover Street were.................... yesterday.','[\"robbed\", \"murdered\", \"broken into\", \"stolen\"]','robbed','\"Robbed\" → soygun anlamındadır; evlerin soyulması uygun ifade.',2,'05e48369-5ea9-4ef0-ab6f-9f5d29358929'),('47c539a8-abc3-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','I lost my job last month. I need some money for my rent and I\'m thinking of ..................some from my father.','[\"lending\", \"borrowing\", \"wasting\", \"owing\"]','borrowing','\