]','at','\"Doğru preposition: good at (bir şeyde iyi olmak). Good in / good of bu bağlamda yanlış olur.\"',1,'125bdad3-eb41-44f1-9ff9-a8cf4f9cae4f'),('493c8494-8e95-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','I am writing my CV. I am looking …. a job?','[\"in\",\"of\",\"on\",\"for\",\"with\"]','for','\"Doğru kullanım: look for (aramak). I am looking for a job.\"',1,'125bdad3-eb41-44f1-9ff9-a8cf4f9cae4f'),('493c86ba-8e95-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','We’re ……….. together for watching a theatre play with my colleagues next Friday. Would you like …… ?','[\"get / to join\",\"getting / to join\",\"got / to join\",\"getting to / join\",\"getting / joined\"]','getting / to join','\"Doğru ifade: We’re getting together … Would you like to join? (Bir araya geliyoruz, katılmak ister misin?).\"',1,'125bdad3-eb41-44f1-9ff9-a8cf4f9cae4f'),('49962fc2-8e67-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','Jordan ….... worry so much. This is his first job application and he can apply for another one.','[\"can\",\"have to\",\"don’t need to\",\"couldn’t\",\"doesn’t need to\"]','doesn’t need to','\"Doğru kullanım: Jordan doesn’t need to worry (endişelenmesine gerek yok).\"',2,'24c604e2-b224-4335-9c8a-02ad2dcc28b3'),('49967626-8e67-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','Apparently, the passenger.……...when his passport…………. .','[\"is being slept/was stolen\",\"sleeping/would be stolen\",\"have slept/has been stolen\",\"slept/would have stolen\",\"was sleeping/was stolen\"]','was sleeping/was stolen','\"Past Continuous + Past Simple: He was sleeping when his passport was stolen.\"',2,'24c604e2-b224-4335-9c8a-02ad2dcc28b3'),('49967a18-8e67-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','Sarah was raised by her grandparents. That’s why she is fond ............ her grandmother.','[\"in\",\"at\",\"of\",\"to\",\"by\"]','of','\"Correct preposition: be fond of (birine/bir şeye düşkün olmak).\"',2,'24c604e2-b224-4335-9c8a-02ad2dcc28b3'),('49967b94-8e67-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','I have a brother who lives in Canada. I don’t see him very often but we ………… by e-mail and phone.','[\"ce