9d776cb9790','I don\'t have time to hear every detail, so I\'d just like you to ---- the report.','[\"extend\", \"declare\", \"summarise\", \"admit\", \"simplify\"]','summarise','“Summarise the report” = raporu özetlemek kalıbı.',3,'6af397dd-a38a-448d-a77d-caf8d7d9dbef'),('80d6d262-ac7a-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','The teacher asked the students to ---- their homework at the end of the lesson.','[\"bring about\", \"look after\", \"get over\", \"give in\", \"set up\"]','give in','Britanya İngilizcesinde ödev “hand in / give in” edilir.',3,'6af397dd-a38a-448d-a77d-caf8d7d9dbef'),('80d6d3f2-ac7a-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','\"Jack the Ripper\" was one of the most famous murderers of all time, and his ---- were all young women in East London.','[\"conquerors\", \"victims\", \"residents\", \"survivors\", \"bystanders\"]','victims','Kurbanlar = “victims”.',3,'6af397dd-a38a-448d-a77d-caf8d7d9dbef'),('80d6d55a-ac7a-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','Because India was formerly a British colony, there is still a British-based system of education there and English is the most ---- spoken second language.','[\"presently\", \"permanently\", \"formally\", \"adequately\", \"widely\"]','widely','“Widely spoken” sık kullanılan kalıptır.',3,'6af397dd-a38a-448d-a77d-caf8d7d9dbef'),('80d6d6f4-ac7a-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','When there is something big that needs repairing in the house, it is usually more economical to ---- the tools than to buy them, as you may only need them once or twice.','[\"hire\", \"lend\", \"charge\", \"purchase\", \"rent\"]','rent','“Rent/hire tools” mümkündür; burada “rent” daha yaygındır.',3,'6af397dd-a38a-448d-a77d-caf8d7d9dbef'),('80d6d866-ac7a-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','You should have seen the ---- on Sheila\'s face when she found the frog in her bag. She looked so surprised!','[\"motion\", \"expression\", \"hazard\", \"description\", \"scar\"]','expression','Yüz ifadesi = “expression”.',3,'6af397dd-a38a-448d-a77d-caf8d7d9dbef'),('80d6dc1c-ac7a-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','To lose weight, you have to ---- sugar and other sweet things.','[\"look forward to\", \"come up with\", \"calm down\", \"cut down on\", \"make up\"]','cut down on','“Cut down on sugar” doğal kalıptır (tüketimi azaltmak).',3,'6af397dd-a38a-448d-a77d-caf8d7d9dbef'),('83dfe77e-8b31-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','You’ll not have to pay a fine ..........','[\"if you bring the books to the library tomorrow\", \"when you drive over the speed limit\", \"unless you have your driving licence with you\", \"because the library opens at 10 o’clock on Saturdays\"]','if you bring the books to the library tomorrow','Kitapları yarın kütüphaneye geri getirirsen ceza ödemek zorunda kalmazsın. Koşul cümlesi (if-clause).',3,'0c5f6d1d-1a1a-4879-8e5e-71efa44d5b40'),('83e00a38-8b31-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','Remember to take some extra food with you ..........','[\"so the children may get hungry\", \"as it was too late to find an open market\", \"in case we have to stay there longer than expected\", \"because of the long and tiring journey\"]','in case we have to stay there longer than expected','Beklenenden daha uzun süre kalmamız gerekirse diye ekstra yiyecek almayı unutma. \"In case\" olası durum için tedbir ifade eder.',3,'0c5f6d1d-1a1a-4879-8e5e-71efa44d5b40'),('83e00cf4-8b31-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','Despite his kind and friendly behaviour ..........','[\"he is the least liked member of the family\", \"he never lies to anybody on any subject\", \"his family is the biggest in this town\", \"everybody admires him\"]','he is the least liked member of the family','Nazik ve samimi davranmasına rağmen ailenin en az sevilen üyesidir. \"Despite\" zıtlık ifade eder.',3,'0c5f6d1d-1a1a-4879-8e5e-71efa44d5b40'),('83e00e66-8b31-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','If James had saved enough money last year, ..........','[\"he still can’t pay the bill\", \"he would have gone to Europe for his holiday this year\", \"he had been staying in a big hotel\", \"he might be able to buy a car then\"]','he would have gone to Europe for his holiday this year','James geçen yıl yeterince para biriktirseydi bu yıl Avrupa tatiline gidebilirdi. Üçüncü tip koşul cümlesi (If + past perfect, would have + V3).',3,'0c5f6d1d-1a1a-4879-8e5e-71efa44d5b40'),('863a0494-8c46-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','John: _____ do you visit your grandparents? Ann: Once or twice a month.','[\"How often\",\"When\",\"What\",\"Where\"]','How often','\"Sıklık sorusu: How often do you visit...?\"',3,'0c5f6d1d-1a1a-4879-8e5e-71efa44d5b40'),('863a5e4e-8c46-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','Someone is calling. They can’t answer the phone because they _____ dinner.','[\"have\",\"having\",\"are having\",\"had\"]','are having','\"Şu anda devam eden eylem: they are having dinner.\"',3,'0c5f6d1d-1a1a-4879-8e5e-71efa44d5b40'),('863a61dc-8c46-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','We are going to make a cake. We need _____ milk for the recipe.','[\"a\",\"an\",\"some\",\"any\"]','some','\"Belirsiz miktarda süt: some milk.\"',3,'0c5f6d1d-1a1a-4879-8e5e-71efa44d5b40'),('863a651a-8c46-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','There _____ any cars fifty years ago. However, we can’t find enough parking space now.','[\"aren’t\",\"weren’t\",\"wasn’t\",\"aren’t\"]','weren’t','\"Geçmişte yoktu: There weren’t any cars.\"',3,'0c5f6d1d-1a1a-4879-8e5e-71efa44d5b40'),('863a6858-8c46-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','These kids enjoy _____ video games. They do not play outside much.','[\"Play\",\"played\",\"playing\",\"plays\"]','playing','\"Enjoy + Ving: enjoy playing.\"',3,'0c5f6d1d-1a1a-4879-8e5e-71efa44d5b40'),('863a6aba-8c46-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','He _____ to the market two hours _____. He hasn’t come back yet.','[\"went/ago\",\"goes/ago\",\"go/before\",\"went/before\"]','went/ago','\"Past simple: went ... two hours ago.\"',3,'0c5f6d1d-1a1a-4879-8e5e-71efa44d5b40'),('8d9cac5e-8d87-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','My father is one of _________ people who work too hard and never think of ________ else but work.','[\"that / something\",\"these / nothing\",\"those / anything\",\"others / somebody\"]','those / anything','\"Doğru ifade: one of those people ... never think of anything else but work.\"',4,'356d75e5-4127-4e2c-8785-8d613234b516'),('8d9cd74c-8d87-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','Three were three issues to be discussed on the agenda. One of them was health, ______ one was education and _______ was social security.','[\"other / another\",\"another / the other\",\"the other / the other\",\"another / other\"]','the other / the other','\"Üç şeyden bahsediliyorsa: biri sağlık, diğeri eğitim, öteki sosyal güvenlik → the other ... the other.\"',4,'356d75e5-4127-4e2c-8785-8d613234b516'),('8d9cdc7e-8d87-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','Reiki, which is a method of stress reduction that ______ healing, __________ in use more than 90 years.','[\"is also promoting / is\",\"will also promote / is being\",\"has also promoted / was\",\"also promotes / has been\"]','also promotes / has been','\"Doğru yapı: also promotes (genel bilgi) ... has been in use (90 yıldır kullanılıyor).\"',4,'356d75e5-4127-4e2c-8785-8d613234b516'),('8d9cdfe4-8d87-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','Having fallen down in front of the audience, the dancer ______ embarrassed; however, he went on dancing as if nothing ________.','[\"was / had happened\",\"was / is happening\",\"had been / had happened\",\"is / had happened\"]','was / had happened','\"Geçmiş zaman + geçmişten önceki olay: was embarrassed ... as if nothing had happened.\"',4,'356d75e5-4127-4e2c-8785-8d613234b516'),('8d9d0a14-8d87-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','It is predicted that we ________ 60 % of the world’s coral reefs by the time the authorities _______ some action.','[\"destroyed / had taken\",\"will have destroyed / take\",\"will destroy / will take\",\"had destroyed / have taken\"]','will have destroyed / take','\"By the time → gelecek mükemmel + geniş zaman: will have destroyed ... take.\"',4,'356d75e5-4127-4e2c-8785-8d613234b516'),('8d9d0bf4-8d87-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','Any food dropped onto the floor or ground ____ if it ____ up before 5 seconds has elapsed, since it is believed that the food cannot be contaminated at such a rapid rate.','[\"could have eaten / had picked\",\"must be eating / had to pick\",\"might be eaten / would have picked\",\"can be eaten / has been picked\"]','can be eaten / has been picked','\"Genel inanç: can be eaten if it has been picked up (5 saniye kuralı).\"',4,'356d75e5-4127-4e2c-8785-8d613234b516'),('8d9d0d48-8d87-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','Stephen Hawking, who________ to be the world’s greatest living scientist, ______ as having motor neuron disease when he was 21.','[\"considered / diagnosed\",\"is considered / was diagnosed\",\"was considered / diagnosed\",\"is being considered / has diagnosed\"]','is considered / was diagnosed','\"Doğru kullanım: is considered (şimdi) ... was diagnosed (geçmişte teşhis edildi).\"',4,'356d75e5-4127-4e2c-8785-8d613234b516'),('8d9d0e7e-8d87-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','If the project ________, you should have one of the assistants ____ it to the director immediately.','[\"has been completed / send\",\"is completed / sending\",\"completed / to send\",\"had completed / send\"]','has been completed / send','\"Present perfect passive: has been completed ... have sb do sth → have one of the assistants send.\"',4,'356d75e5-4127-4e2c-8785-8d613234b516'),('8d9d0faa-8d87-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','In Ancient Egypt young men _______ their own careers, instead, they very often ____ the family trade or profession.','[\"weren’t usually chosen / had followed\",\"hadn’t usually chosen / were followed\",\"had usually chosen / followed\",\"didn’t usually choose / followed\"]','didn’t usually choose / followed','\"Geçmişte alışkanlık: didn’t usually choose ... followed.\"',4,'356d75e5-4127-4e2c-8785-8d613234b516'),('8d9d11bc-8d87-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','While this museum building _______, the collection _______ in the state museum.','[\"is renovated / will temporarily house\",\"is renovating / will temporarily be housed\",\"has been renovated / is temporarily housing\",\"is being renovated / will temporarily be housed\"]','is being renovated / will temporarily be housed','\"Devam eden pasif + gelecek pasif: is being renovated ... will temporarily be housed.\"',4,'356d75e5-4127-4e2c-8785-8d613234b516'),('8e42200c-aad9-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','What is Jennifer _______ now? \nA) doing \nB) is doing \nC) does \nD) do','[\"doing\", \"is doing\", \"does\", \"do\"]','doing','“Now” ifadesi şimdiki zamanı (Present Continuous) gösterir. Bu yüzden “What is Jennifer doing now?” doğru ifadedir.',1,'cce5cff5-717d-4a4c-9d72-d554baa5e779'),('9151ebb6-8e45-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','Tomorrow is the last day of the school. After the last exam, you want to have a party with your friends at your home. You want to politely invite your friends to your house for the party and you say:','[\"We have a party tomorrow. Everybody has to come to my house after the exam.\",\"I thought it would be a nice idea to have a party after the exam. Would you like to come?\",\"Tomorrow, I will organize a party at my house. If you don’t come, I will not speak to you again.\",\"My parents won’t be at home tomorrow. Because you are my friends, all of you must come to my party.\"]','I thought it would be a nice idea to have a party after the exam. Would you like to come?','\"Doğru cevap nazik bir davet cümlesidir: Would you like to come? polite invitation.\"',3,'cf4e6d96-0c6c-4a7d-8576-c7f376611f51'),('915292c8-8e45-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','You want to buy a dress for your brother’s wedding and you go to a shop. You find a nice dress and you like it a lot, but it’s green and you don’t like the color. So, you call the shop assistant and say:','[\"This dress doesn’t look good on me. Do you have any different type?\",\"I like this one a lot but I want a different color. Do you have it in blue?\",\"I don’t like any of your dresses. I should find a new shop.\",\"I like the green dress. Can I try on a medium size of it?\"]','I like this one a lot but I want a different color. Do you have it in blue?','\"Doğru cevap: Rengi beğenmediğini kibarca belirtip başka renk isteme.\"',3,'cf4e6d96-0c6c-4a7d-8576-c7f376611f51'),('9152acf4-8e45-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','You are in the middle of the proficiency exam. Unfortunately, your pencil is broken and you do not have an extra one. You go to the teacher and respectfully say:','[\"Teacher, bring me a pencil. Mine is broken.\",\"I want a new pencil or I will stop and leave.\",\"Could you please give me a new pencil? I forgot to have an extra with me.\",\"Teacher, you must give me your pencil. Otherwise I can’t go on my exam.\"]','Could you please give me a new pencil? I forgot to have an extra with me.','\"Doğru cevap: polite request → Could you please...?\"',3,'cf4e6d96-0c6c-4a7d-8576-c7f376611f51'),('9152b17c-8e45-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','Your best friend’s birthday was last week but you forgot it and she is angry with you. She has not talked to you for a week, so you want to apologize for your mistake and you say:','[\"Sibel, I am terribly sorry because I forgot your birthday. Forgive me, please.\",\"Sibel, I heard that your birthday was last week. Is it true?\",\"Sibel, why don’t you talk to me? Did I make a mistake?\",\"Sibel, you should forget my mistake, it wasn’t a big mistake, was it?\"]','Sibel, I am terribly sorry because I forgot your birthday. Forgive me, please.','\"Doğru cevap: özür dileme ve affetmesini isteme.\"',3,'cf4e6d96-0c6c-4a7d-8576-c7f376611f51'),('9152b3ac-8e45-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','................................................. you won’t catch the train.','[\"Unless you rush to the station\",\"While you are looking for a taxi\",\"Since you were in a hurry\",\"Whenever you try hard\"]','Unless you rush to the station','\"Doğru kullanım: Unless (olmazsa)... you won’t catch the train.\"',3,'cf4e6d96-0c6c-4a7d-8576-c7f376611f51'),('9152b53c-8e45-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','................................................. before she came to Turkey.','[\"Sally speaks three languages\",\"Denise already spoke some Turkish\",\"My sister often visits me\",\"My aunt has written several books\"]','Denise already spoke some Turkish','\"Zaman uyumu: before she came to Turkey → geçmiş zaman. Doğru cevap: already spoke.\"',3,'cf4e6d96-0c6c-4a7d-8576-c7f376611f51'),('9152b870-8e45-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','The weather was so cold .................................................','[\"until the spring comes\",\"that I decided not to walk to school\",\"because it is snowing heavily\",\"when the wind blows hard\"]','that I decided not to walk to school','\"So ... that yapısı: so cold that I decided not to walk.\"',3,'cf4e6d96-0c6c-4a7d-8576-c7f376611f51'),('9153ce72-8e45-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','In the end I went by bus .................................................','[\"as I missed the train\",\"since I feel very tired\",\"that it stops so near the library\",\"because there isn’t a taxi available\"]','as I missed the train','\"Sebep-sonuç bağlacı: went by bus as I missed the train.\"',3,'cf4e6d96-0c6c-4a7d-8576-c7f376611f51'),('9153d034-8e45-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','The better I get to know him .................................................','[\"the more reliable were the data\",\"the less I like him\",\"I can’t stand him\",\"he seemed more polite\"]','the less I like him','\"The ... the ... comparative yapısı: The better I get to know him, the less I like him.\"',3,'cf4e6d96-0c6c-4a7d-8576-c7f376611f51'),('adcfb2c0-ac84-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','The efforts of humanity to find the truth ________ trial and error have broadened the boundaries ________ science.','[\"with / in\", \"of / at\", \"by / of\", \"for / on\", \"through / for\"]','by / of','Doğal kalıplar: \"by trial and error\" ve \"boundaries of science\".',1,'00a862d7-735d-4c17-bbaf-5d6889aa2bd8'),('add07944-ac84-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','________ the opening of the new restaurant, I suffered ________ a terrible headache.','[\"At / from\", \"In / of\", \"For / on\", \"On / -\", \"By / in\"]','At / from','Etkinlik zamanı \"at the opening\"; \"suffer from\" doğru kullanımdır.',1,'00a862d7-735d-4c17-bbaf-5d6889aa2bd8'),('add07bd8-ac84-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','________ Bangladesh\'s wells were full of too much arsenic, up to 80 million people may already be poisoned.','[\"Nonetheless\", \"Therefore\", \"However\", \"Consequently\", \"Because\"]','Because','Sonuç cümlesinin nedenini veren bağlaç: \"Because … may already be …\".',1,'00a862d7-735d-4c17-bbaf-5d6889aa2bd8'),('add0a05e-ac84-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','The reason of the death of the old lady wasn\'t cancer. It wasn\'t a heart disease, ________.','[\"nor\", \"both\", \"neither\", \"either\", \"also\"]','either','Olumsuz cümlenin sonuna \"either\" gelir: \"wasn\'t …, either.\"',1,'00a862d7-735d-4c17-bbaf-5d6889aa2bd8'),('add0a284-ac84-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','________ a study published last week, regional changes have increased in plant growth around the world.','[\"But for\", \"Up to\", \"According to\", \"In turn\", \"After all\"]','According to','Kaynak belirtmede \"According to …\".',1,'00a862d7-735d-4c17-bbaf-5d6889aa2bd8'),('add0a446-ac84-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','Scientists have reached the point ________ they have begun to discover the existence of it.','[\"where\", \"that\", \"when\", \"which\", \"who\"]','where','\"reach the point where …\" kalıbı kullanılır.',1,'00a862d7-735d-4c17-bbaf-5d6889aa2bd8'),('add13cda-ac84-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','Exactly ________ the brain consolidates and retrieves lost memories during sleep is still a mystery.','[\"what\", \"why\", \"where\", \"how\", \"when\"]','how','Soru kelimesi + yan tümce özne olur: \"Exactly how … is …\".',1,'00a862d7-735d-4c17-bbaf-5d6889aa2bd8'),('ae8e3166-aaca-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','Mike _______ to write his research project yet. It will be difficult for him to finish it in time.','[\"didn’t start\", \"wasn’t starting\", \"doesn’t start\", \"hasn’t started\"]','hasn’t started','Present Perfect: “hasn’t started” shows an unfinished action up to now.',3,'6b3a591d-4c46-4bb7-b079-12887fb27fdd'),('ae8e9ec6-aaca-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','Mark is ill ________ he hasn’t finished his work yet.','[\"so\", \"because\", \"while\", \"before\"]','because','“Because” gives the reason why something happens.',3,'6b3a591d-4c46-4bb7-b079-12887fb27fdd'),('ae8ea510-aaca-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','Miriam _______ up yet. I think she ______ the bus.','[\"hasn’t woken / will miss\", \"didn’t wake / misses\", \"hasn’t woken / was missing\", \"isn’t waking / misses\"]','hasn’t woken / will miss','Future prediction based on present perfect situation.',3,'6b3a591d-4c46-4bb7-b079-12887fb27fdd'),('ae8ea9ac-aaca-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','If Eric ________ that house in London, he _______ to London in a month.','[\"buys / moved\", \"is buying / has moved\", \"bought / is moving\", \"buys / will move\"]','buys / will move','First Conditional: “If + present simple, will + verb”.',3,'6b3a591d-4c46-4bb7-b079-12887fb27fdd'),('ae8eacb8-aaca-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','They _______ visit Burma last weekend because they ________ out of town all weekend.','[\"didn’t / did\", \"wasn’t / was\", \"weren’t / were\", \"didn’t / were\"]','didn’t / were','Past tense negative with “didn’t” and “were”.',3,'6b3a591d-4c46-4bb7-b079-12887fb27fdd'),('ae8eb00a-aaca-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','Julia usually _______ to school but today it is warm outside so she__________ to school.','[\"drives / walks\", \"drive / walk\", \"drives / is walking\", \"drive / is walking\"]','drives / is walking','Present Simple for habits, Present Continuous for actions happening now.',3,'6b3a591d-4c46-4bb7-b079-12887fb27fdd'),('ae8eb26c-aaca-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','Don’t make noise! Your brother________ his homework.','[\"is doing\", \"did\", \"are doing\", \"does\"]','is doing','Present Continuous for actions happening right now.',3,'6b3a591d-4c46-4bb7-b079-12887fb27fdd'),('ae8eb618-aaca-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','I_____ in a small village but now I live in a big city.','[\"went\", \"born\", \"grew up\", \"loved\"]','grew up','“Grow up” means to spend your childhood in a place.',3,'6b3a591d-4c46-4bb7-b079-12887fb27fdd'),('ae8f2e72-aaca-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','Nick arrived to the stadium while we __________ match with the team-Angels.','[\"played\", \"were playing\", \"play\", \"are playing\"]','were playing','Past Continuous describes an action in progress when another happened.',3,'6b3a591d-4c46-4bb7-b079-12887fb27fdd'),('ae8f308e-aaca-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','Our company ___________ a new contract with a Japan company next year.','[\"signs\", \"signed\", \"is going to sign\", \"are going to sign\"]','is going to sign','Future plan using “be going to”.',3,'6b3a591d-4c46-4bb7-b079-12887fb27fdd'),('b3024d1a-abc2-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','I …………… home when a car..................... next to me. It was him.','[\"walked/was stopping\", \"am walking/ stops\", \"have walked/ stopped\", \"was walking/ stopped\"]','was walking/ stopped','\"Past Continuous\" ile geçmişte devam eden bir eylem, \"was walking\" uygundur; ardından \"stopped\" ile aniden olan olayı belirtir.',2,'05e48369-5ea9-4ef0-ab6f-9f5d29358929'),('b302738a-abc2-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','I\'m really looking forward to …………… everyday at the beach and.....................suntan, and I\'d like …………… how to dive.','[\"spend/ get/ to learn\", \"spend/ getting/ learning\", \"spending/ getting/ to learn\", \"spending/ to get/ learning\"]','spending/ getting/ to learn','\"Look forward to\" + gerund (Ving) kullanılır, yani \"spending\". \"Get a suntan\" ve \"learn how\" yapılarıyla uyumlu.',2,'05e48369-5ea9-4ef0-ab6f-9f5d29358929'),('b3028a32-abc2-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','Beth\'s much …………… easy-going and she isn\'t as..................... as Carol, but sometimes they are both as..................... as each other.','[\"most/ more selfish/ moodier\", \"- / selfish/ the moodiest\", \"more/ the most selfish/ moodiest\", \"more/ selfish/ moody\"]','more/ selfish/ moody','Karşılaştırma yapısı: \"more easy-going\" → \"daha rahat\", \"selfish/ moody\" doğru sıfat biçimlerini verir.',2,'05e48369-5ea9-4ef0-ab6f-9f5d29358929'),('b3028ffa-abc2-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','Excuse me, how far .....................from the hotel to the city centre?','[\"it is\", \"is it\", \"there is\", \"is there\"]','is it','Soru cümlelerinde doğru kelime sırası: \"how far is it\" → mesafe sorusu.',2,'05e48369-5ea9-4ef0-ab6f-9f5d29358929'),('b30294c8-abc2-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','The news.................... very disappointing yesterday.','[\"were\", \"was\", \"used to be\", \"is\"]','was','\"News\" tekil kabul edilir, geçmiş zaman için \"was\" kullanılır.',2,'05e48369-5ea9-4ef0-ab6f-9f5d29358929'),('b30296f8-abc2-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','-\" How long ................... you ....................in Ankara?\" -\"For a few days. I expect to be back here before the weekend.\"','[\"do/stay\", \"did/stay\", \"were/staying\", \"will/stay\"]','did/stay','Geçmiş zaman sorusu → \"did you stay\" doğru kullanımdır.',2,'05e48369-5ea9-4ef0-ab6f-9f5d29358929'),('b30298ba-abc2-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','I\'ve never .................... to .....................USA.','[\"gone/the\", \"gone/- (no article)\", \"been/the\", \"been/- (no article)\"]','been/- (no article)','\"Present Perfect\" yapısında \"been to\" doğru kullanım; ülke adlarında article gerekmez.',2,'05e48369-5ea9-4ef0-ab6f-9f5d29358929'),('b3029aae-abc2-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','Please, don\'t walk so........................ Remember, I\'m 50 years older than you.','[\"quick\", \"fastly\", \"fast\", \"slow\"]','fast','\"Fast\" zarf olarak kullanılır; \"quickly\" da olabilir ama buradaki bağlamda \"fast\" daha doğal.',2,'05e48369-5ea9-4ef0-ab6f-9f5d29358929'),('b3029c84-abc2-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','How .....................does it cost to go to Meydanbaşı from Yenişehir?','[\"much\", \"often\", \"far\", \"long\"]','much','Soru “ne kadar maliyet” ile ilgili → \"how much\" doğru ifadedir.',2,'05e48369-5ea9-4ef0-ab6f-9f5d29358929'),('b3029eaa-abc2-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','When a price decreases, the price ……………','[\"becomes less\", \"becomes more\", \"changes often\", \"stays the same\"]','becomes less','\"Price decreases\" → fiyat düşer, doğru ifade \"becomes less\".',2,'05e48369-5ea9-4ef0-ab6f-9f5d29358929'),('bad84d20-8e42-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','Students in Turkey, who want to attend a _______ university, need to study really _______ to pass all their exams.','[\"good / hard\",\"well / harder\",\"best / hardest\",\"better / the hardest\"]','good / hard','\"Sıfat + zarf: a good university, study hard.\"',2,'90d6832d-a7a4-4e19-b580-8bff59fb52e1'),('bad88aba-8e42-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','That is _______ frightening horror film I’ve ever seen. It was really _____.','[\"least / boring\",\"the least / boring\",\"less / boring\",\"the least / bored\"]','the least / boring','\"Superlative: the least frightening, it was boring.\"',2,'90d6832d-a7a4-4e19-b580-8bff59fb52e1'),('bad88df8-8e42-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','________ people hate driving in İstanbul. There is ________ traffic.','[\"Much / enough\",\"Lots of / too many\",\"A lot of / very\",\"Most / too much\"]','Most / too much','\"Most people, too much traffic.\"',2,'90d6832d-a7a4-4e19-b580-8bff59fb52e1'),('bad8914a-8e42-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','Can you see _______ boy playing football over there? He is ________ one who broke my car’s windscreen yesterday.','[\"the / the\",\"a / ___\",\"the / __\",\"a / the\"]','the / the','\"Definite article: the boy, the one.\"',2,'90d6832d-a7a4-4e19-b580-8bff59fb52e1'),('bad89406-8e42-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','The professor ______ teaches Chemistry 110 is an excellent lecturer and his classroom is full of students ________ grades are always high.','[\"that / of whom\",\"who / whose\",\"whom / which\",\"whose / whom\"]','who / whose','\"Relative clause: professor who teaches…, students whose grades…\" ',2,'90d6832d-a7a4-4e19-b580-8bff59fb52e1'),('bad89618-8e42-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','I don’t know the day ________ our new neighbor will get married.','[\"what\",\"who\",\"where\",\"when\"]','when','\"Relative adverb: the day when.\"',2,'90d6832d-a7a4-4e19-b580-8bff59fb52e1'),('bad8b26a-8e42-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','________ answering a question in the test, you should think all the options.','[\"After\",\"Meanwhile\",\"While\",\"As\"]','Before','\"Doğru kullanım: Before answering a question, …\"',2,'90d6832d-a7a4-4e19-b580-8bff59fb52e1'),('bad8b62a-8e42-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','Some people don’t want to go to the circus, ________ they don’t like to see wild animals in captivity.','[\"while\",\"because\",\"but\",\"although\"]','because','\"Reason clause: because they don’t like…\" ',2,'90d6832d-a7a4-4e19-b580-8bff59fb52e1'),('bad8b9a4-8e42-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','After the earthquake, many people _________ go back to their houses so they slept in the fields.','[\"can’t\",\"shouldn’t\",\"didn’t have to\",\"couldn’t\"]','couldn’t','\"Past ability in negative: couldn’t go back.\"',2,'90d6832d-a7a4-4e19-b580-8bff59fb52e1'),('bad8d84e-8e42-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','My cousin is a millionaire. She ________ work but she does because she just loves her job.','[\"doesn’t have to\",\"mustn’t\",\"had to\",\"might\"]','doesn’t have to','\"Lazım değil: doesn’t have to work.\"',2,'90d6832d-a7a4-4e19-b580-8bff59fb52e1'),('bad945ea-8e42-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','Old people usually pretend ________ asleep when they don’t want _______ what is being said to them.','[\"to being / to having\",\"being / hearing\",\"being / to hear\",\"to be / to hear\"]','to be / to hear','\"Infinitive structure: pretend to be…, don’t want to hear…\" ',2,'90d6832d-a7a4-4e19-b580-8bff59fb52e1'),('bdc9f7b0-8e3b-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','I _________ very excited about the new promotion and I __________ forward to taking on more responsibilities.','[\"am feeling / looked\",\"was feeling / will be looking\",\"will feel / look\",\"feel / am looking\"]','feel / am looking','\"Doğru kullanım: present simple + present continuous → I feel very excited ... and I am looking forward to ...\"',4,'e6eec0bb-827c-4a91-b0fb-540f12289300'),('bdd5fd5c-aaca-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','Susan: Hi, Suzie. You look tired. _________________? Suzie: Oh, I cleaned all my room yesterday. That’s why.','[\"What’s the matter\", \"I’m sorry for that\", \"How was the interview\", \"Why not going home\"]','What’s the matter','Used to ask someone why they look tired, sad, or worried.',3,'6b3a591d-4c46-4bb7-b079-12887fb27fdd'),('bdd6c462-aaca-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','A: Mum, did you hear the news about Jessica? B: ______________________? A: She got married and is moving to France.','[\"What’s the matter\", \"What do you mean\", \"That’s wonderful\", \"How interesting\"]','What do you mean','“What do you mean?” is used to ask for clarification.',3,'6b3a591d-4c46-4bb7-b079-12887fb27fdd'),('bdd6c872-aaca-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','Jordan: Hi Jordan. ______________? Alice: Not much. I’m doing some decoration at home.','[\"Help yourself\", \"How much is your home\", \"I don’t think so\", \"What’s new\"]','What’s new','Common greeting used to ask what’s happening in someone’s life.',3,'6b3a591d-4c46-4bb7-b079-12887fb27fdd'),('bdd70440-aaca-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','A: Are you ready to order? B: Can I have some cake, please? A: ____________________? B: Coffee, please.','[\"What’s good here\", \"Can I have some coffee\", \"Anything to drink\", \"Here you go, enjoy\"]','Anything to drink','Used by waiters to ask if the customer wants a drink.',3,'6b3a591d-4c46-4bb7-b079-12887fb27fdd'),('bdd709fe-aaca-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','A: I’m so happy. I finally passed the driving exam. B: ______________________.','[\"How awful\", \"That’s terrible\", \"Congratulations\", \"How interesting\"]','Congratulations','Used to express happiness for someone’s success.',3,'6b3a591d-4c46-4bb7-b079-12887fb27fdd'),('bdd73708-aaca-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','A: Could I borrow your pencil, please? B: _______________________. A: Thanks a lot.','[\"Of course not\", \"Here you are\", \"I’m having some problems\", \"I need some help\"]','Here you are','Common polite response when giving something to someone.',3,'6b3a591d-4c46-4bb7-b079-12887fb27fdd'),('bdd76200-aaca-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','A: ________________? B: Really? You’re kidding! Did you see my sister’s cat Were they home last night Did you hear that Andrew quit his job Did you know that guy','[\"Did you see my sister’s cat\", \"Were they home last night\", \"Did you hear that Andrew quit his job\", \"Did you know that guy\"]','Did you hear that Andrew quit his job','“Did you hear that...” introduces surprising or interesting news.',3,'6b3a591d-4c46-4bb7-b079-12887fb27fdd'),('bdd7ecf2-aaca-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','A: __________________________ B: It was good but the weather was rainy all day.','[\"How was your vacation?\", \"Just my luck!\", \"What’s the weather like?\", \"That’s too bad.\"]','How was your vacation?','Used to ask about someone’s holiday experience.',3,'6b3a591d-4c46-4bb7-b079-12887fb27fdd'),('bdd7ef72-aaca-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','A: Hello, can I help you? B: ________________________? A: Yes, we have. This medicine is really good.','[\"How about some soup\", \"Are you ill\", \"Do you have anything for a cold\", \"What’s the problem\"]','Do you have anything for a cold','Common pharmacy question to ask if a medicine exists for a specific illness.',3,'6b3a591d-4c46-4bb7-b079-12887fb27fdd'),('bdd7f1e8-aaca-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','A: Are you OK? B: No, I’m not. Thieves broke into my house and stole my laptop. A: Oh my goodness! _________________','[\"That’s perfect\", \"I’m sorry to hear that\", \"Guess what\", \"How wonderful\"]','I’m sorry to hear that','Used to express sympathy when hearing bad news.',3,'6b3a591d-4c46-4bb7-b079-12887fb27fdd'),('be0d3ece-8e97-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','David suffers from asthma and he _____ breathes during attacks.','[\"darkly\",\"merely\",\"virtually\",\"arguably\",\"barely\"]','barely','\"Barely breathes = neredeyse hiç nefes alamaz.\"',3,'d475b5bf-9c5e-4b8f-a462-40a9e5132dd1'),('be0d8d5c-8e97-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','His family describes Simon as a/an _____ man since he is not proud.','[\"humble\",\"insistent\",\"superficial\",\"fearsome\",\"hazardous\"]','humble','\"Humble = alçakgönüllü, gururlu olmayan.\"',3,'d475b5bf-9c5e-4b8f-a462-40a9e5132dd1'),('be0d9e78-8e97-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','In this neighbourhood, it is believed that _____ what security precautions you take, thieves can always find a way to break into houses.','[\"as though\",\"no matter\",\"although\",\"nevertheless\",\"otherwise\"]','no matter','\"No matter what precautions you take = hangi önlemi alırsan al.\"',3,'d475b5bf-9c5e-4b8f-a462-40a9e5132dd1'),('be0db3d6-8e97-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','Our football players _____ for almost two months by the time the new season _____ in December, 2019.','[\"are training/started\",\"had trained/have started\",\"have been training/will start\",\"will have been training/starts\",\"are going to train/will have started\"]','will have been training/starts','\"By the time + Present Simple → Future Perfect Continuous.\"',3,'d475b5bf-9c5e-4b8f-a462-40a9e5132dd1'),('be0db6d8-8e97-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','Look what it says on the wall: “The gas tank _____ before the rental car _____ to the customer, this is our company policy.”','[\"was filled/has delivered\",\"will have been filled/is being delivered\",\"is filled/is delivered\",\"must be filled/delivers\",\"has been filled/has been delivered\"]','will have been filled/is being delivered','\"Araba müşteriye teslim EDİLİRKEN depo DOLMUŞ olacak.\"',3,'d475b5bf-9c5e-4b8f-a462-40a9e5132dd1'),('be0db9bc-8e97-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','Don’t you wish you _____ that other job offer, then you _____ problems with your manager now.','[\"will accept/won\'t be having\",\"had accepted/wouldn\'t be having\",\"have accepted/aren’t having\",\"accepted/weren’t having\",\"are accepting/won’t have\"]','had accepted/wouldn\'t be having','\"I wish + Past Perfect → would ... now.\"',3,'d475b5bf-9c5e-4b8f-a462-40a9e5132dd1'),('be0dc22c-8e97-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','Marsel İlhan _____ better in the tennis tournament than I thought he _____, because he got through to the finals.','[\"will play/can\",\"should have played/did\",\"could have played/can\",\"had better play/would\",\"must have played/could\"]','must have played/could','\"Gerçekte beklenenden daha iyi oynadı → must have played ... than I thought he could.\"',3,'d475b5bf-9c5e-4b8f-a462-40a9e5132dd1'),('c47e6908-8b32-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','In China, Japan and other oriental countries, where tea is the national drink, people almost never use sugar in their tea. .......... Most people everywhere want their tea very hot, but many Americans drink iced tea, especially in the summer.','[\"Coffee is a favourite drink of people in all parts of the world.\", \"However in England, where tea is also a national drink, many people use sugar.\", \"Some people put cream and sugar in their coffee.\", \"China is famous for its green tea.\"]','However in England, where tea is also a national drink, many people use sugar.','Çin, Japonya ve diğer doğu ülkelerinde şeker kullanılmaz, ancak İngiltere’de çay milli içecek olduğu halde pek çok kişi şeker kullanır. Bu nedenle doğru seçenek B.',3,'0c5f6d1d-1a1a-4879-8e5e-71efa44d5b40'),('c47ed1fe-8b32-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','My most embarrassing experience happened when I had just left university. I had just started teaching in a secondary school. One morning my alarm clock didn’t ring because I had forgotten to wind it up. I left home in a hurry and rushed to school. ..........','[\"I hadn’t noticed that I had put on one black shoe and one brown shoe.\", \"After two or three minutes, the students began laughing at me.\", \"Though I was late, I had taken all my books with me.\", \"I woke up half past eight and school began at nine.\"]','I hadn’t noticed that I had put on one black shoe and one brown shoe.','En utanç verici deneyimim, bir siyah bir kahverengi ayakkabı giymiş olduğumu fark etmememdi. Bu nedenle doğru seçenek A.',3,'0c5f6d1d-1a1a-4879-8e5e-71efa44d5b40'),('c47edfd2-8b32-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','Most people in Britain find the prices of good restaurants too expensive. Many people are so busy that they don’t have time to cook for themselves. Others live alone and feel it is not worth cooking just for one person. .......... The latest statistics show that the British spend 2.2 billion pounds each year on fast food.','[\"Chinese restaurants, Indian restaurants and hamburger bars are becoming more and more popular.\", \"The British spent over 619 million pounds on fish and chips last year.\", \"This has led to incredible increase in the fast food business.\", \"Many people prefer to eat in the comfort of their homes.\"]','This has led to incredible increase in the fast food business.','Yoğun yaşam ve tek kişi için yemek yapmanın anlamsızlığı, fast food sektöründe büyük bir artışa yol açmıştır. Bu yüzden doğru cevap C.',3,'0c5f6d1d-1a1a-4879-8e5e-71efa44d5b40'),('c47ee392-8b32-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','Over the years many different systems of physical exercise have been designed to improve health and appearance of the body .......... It consists of various exercises.','[\"Everybody should do some kind of exercise to be healthy.\", \"One of the best among them is Hatha Yoga.\", \"The best way to live is to be a good sportsman.\", \"All kinds of exercise must be done carefully and regularly.\"]','One of the best among them is Hatha Yoga.','Vücut sağlığı ve görünümü için tasarlanmış egzersiz sistemlerinden en iyilerinden biri Hatha Yoga’dır. Bu yüzden doğru seçenek B.',3,'0c5f6d1d-1a1a-4879-8e5e-71efa44d5b40'),('c7a9a838-abbf-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','That’s the scientist __________ discovered a new species last year, and her work has inspired many young researchers.','[\"which\", \"who\", \"whose\", \"where\"]','who','“Who” insanlardan bahsederken kullanılır → “the scientist who discovered…”.',2,'031d2262-a41b-475c-bee1-e9a5a439ba5a'),('c7aa2a10-abbf-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','It was __________ an exciting match that the crowd cheered more loudly than ever before.','[\"very\", \"such\", \"so\", \"too\"]','such','“Such + noun” yapısı → “such an exciting match”. “So” sıfatla kullanılır, isimle değil.',2,'031d2262-a41b-475c-bee1-e9a5a439ba5a'),('c7aa2f7e-abbf-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','I’ll send you an email as soon as I ______ (get) home, so you ______ (have) all the details before the meeting, which starts at 3 p.m.','[\"will get / are having\", \"got / have had\", \"get / will have\", \"am getting / would have\"]','get / will have','Zaman yan cümlelerinde “will” kullanılmaz → “as soon as I get”. Ana cümlede “will have”.',2,'031d2262-a41b-475c-bee1-e9a5a439ba5a'),('c7aa47fc-abbf-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','She ______ (fly) to New York next month for a business conference, and she ______ (already book) her flight and hotel.','[\"was going to fly / already booked\", \"will fly / have already booked\", \"flies / had already booked\", \"is flying / has already booked\"]','is flying / has already booked','“Next month” → gelecek planı, “is flying”. “Has already booked” → present perfect, sonucu var.',2,'031d2262-a41b-475c-bee1-e9a5a439ba5a'),('c7aa5620-abbf-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','I won’t go on holiday ____ I save enough money, which might take a few more months.','[\"unless\", \"before\", \"after\", \"as soon as\"]','unless','“Unless” = “if not” yani “...olmazsa”. → “I won’t go unless I save money.”',2,'031d2262-a41b-475c-bee1-e9a5a439ba5a'),('c7aa5aee-abbf-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','By the time you arrive at the airport, I ______ (finish) all the check-in procedures.','[\"will finish\", \"will be finishing\", \"will have finished\", \"will be finished\"]','will have finished','“By the time” → belirli zamana kadar tamamlanmış eylem → future perfect tense.',2,'031d2262-a41b-475c-bee1-e9a5a439ba5a'),('c7aa5f44-abbf-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','The company, ________ employees are highly skilled, is expanding rapidly.','[\"which\", \"whose\", \"that\", \"where\"]','whose','“Whose” = sahiplik bildirir. → “The company whose employees…”',2,'031d2262-a41b-475c-bee1-e9a5a439ba5a'),('c7aa6502-abbf-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','If I ________ (be) more careful while driving, I ________ (not crash) my car last night.','[\"am / wouldn’t have crashed\", \"had been / wouldn’t crash\", \"was / wouldn’t crash\", \"had been / wouldn’t have crashed\"]','had been / wouldn’t have crashed','Geçmişteki pişmanlık → 3. tip koşul → “had been / wouldn’t have crashed”.',2,'031d2262-a41b-475c-bee1-e9a5a439ba5a'),('c7aa6912-abbf-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','If I ________ (be) you, I would take the job offer, as it would be a great opportunity for my career.','[\"am\", \"were\", \"was\", \"would\"]','were','“If I were you” sabit kalıptır. Tavsiye verirken kullanılır.',2,'031d2262-a41b-475c-bee1-e9a5a439ba5a'),('c7aa6e3a-abbf-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','They ________ (prepare) for the upcoming presentation for weeks, and now they are confident about their performance.','[\"have prepared\", \"had prepared\", \"have been preparing\", \"were preparing\"]','have been preparing','“Have been preparing” → süregelen geçmişten bugüne kadar devam eden eylem (present perfect continuous).',2,'031d2262-a41b-475c-bee1-e9a5a439ba5a'),('c9392588-ac6f-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','She visits Muş every summer, ---- her parents live there.','[\"but\", \"unless\", \"because\", \"so\", \"although\"]','because','\"Because\" → nedeni belirtir: Ebeveynleri orada yaşadığı için her yaz Muş’u ziyaret eder.',4,'08aa5752-09aa-45f6-972b-3d893074caa6'),('c939869a-ac6f-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','She ---- a lot of games when she was in the village, but she ---- any more.','[\"had played / wouldn\'t do\", \"used to play / doesn’t\", \"have played / haven\'t done\", \"was playing / hadn\'t done\", \"played / didn\'t\"]','used to play / doesn’t','\"Used to\" geçmişte alışkanlık olan, artık yapılmayan eylemler için kullanılır.',4,'08aa5752-09aa-45f6-972b-3d893074caa6'),('c9398c12-ac6f-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','Don\'t blame ---- for keeping you waiting. It was entirely ---- fault.','[\"me / his\", \"mine / their\", \"her / them\", \"his / my\", \"them / ours\"]','me / his','\"Blame me\" → beni suçla; \"his fault\" → onun hatası anlamındadır.',4,'08aa5752-09aa-45f6-972b-3d893074caa6'),('c9398f1e-ac6f-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','I ---- the holiday in Istanbul, because the weather ---- disappointing.','[\"enjoy / would have been\", \"had enjoyed / has been\", \"have enjoyed / was being\", \"am enjoying / had been\", \"didn’t enjoy / was\"]','didn’t enjoy / was','\"Didn’t enjoy\" geçmişte beğenmemek; \"was disappointing\" → hayal kırıklığıydı.',4,'08aa5752-09aa-45f6-972b-3d893074caa6'),('c939a486-ac6f-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','In general, people in the eastern countries are ---- optimistic about life ---- people in the western countries.','[\"and / but\", \"so / as\", \"both / and\", \"neither / nor\", \"more / than\"]','more / than','\"More ... than\" → karşılaştırma yapar: doğudakiler batıdakilerden daha iyimser.',4,'08aa5752-09aa-45f6-972b-3d893074caa6'),('c939a7f6-ac6f-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','Before going abroad as an Erasmus+ student, a/an ---- letter must be sent by the receiving institution.','[\"strike\", \"conflict\", \"precaution\", \"acceptance\", \"doubt\"]','acceptance','\"Acceptance letter\" → kabul mektubu; Erasmus öncesi gönderilir.',4,'08aa5752-09aa-45f6-972b-3d893074caa6'),('c939abca-ac6f-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','Unfortunately, some of the students at MSU don’t have the courage to go abroad with ---- programmes, such as Erasmus+ and others.','[\"addiction\", \"mobility\", \"urgency\", \"benefit\", \"impression\"]','mobility','\"Mobility programmes\" → öğrenci değişim programları anlamındadır.',4,'08aa5752-09aa-45f6-972b-3d893074caa6'),('c939ae0e-ac6f-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','Foods that were ---- seasonal may be found now throughout the year.','[\"properly\", \"satisfactorily\", \"rapidly\", \"formerly\", \"seriously\"]','formerly','\"Formerly\" → eskiden demektir; artık yıl boyu bulunabiliyor anlamına uyar.',4,'08aa5752-09aa-45f6-972b-3d893074caa6'),('c939b07a-ac6f-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','I wanted to ---- to my friend for using his pen without permission.','[\"apologize\", \"conclude\", \"quarrel\", \"contrast\", \"blame\"]','apologize','\"Apologize\" → özür dilemek; izinsiz kalem kullanmak için uygundur.',4,'08aa5752-09aa-45f6-972b-3d893074caa6'),('c939b2be-ac6f-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','You can certainly trust this friend; she never ---- any secrets.','[\"remembers\", \"tells\", \"prevents\", \"keeps\", \"leaves\"]','tells','\"Tell secrets\" → sır söylemek anlamında; söylemediği için güvenilir biridir.',4,'08aa5752-09aa-45f6-972b-3d893074caa6'),('ca5db0aa-aacb-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','Frank is a _________ person. He always helps his friends and pays for them at restaurants.','[\"lazy\", \"confident\", \"generous\", \"selfish\"]','generous','\"Generous\" means willing to give and share with others.',4,'0c559ccd-2f8e-4644-b642-2f0cac112047'),('ca5ddc4c-aacb-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','The bus leaves downtown at 9:25 and it _____ the city center at 10:05.','[\"departs at\", \"gets to\", \"is\", \"begins\"]','gets to','\"Gets to\" is the phrasal verb used for arriving at a place.',4,'0c559ccd-2f8e-4644-b642-2f0cac112047'),('ca5de2dc-aacb-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','My best friend and I ___________ to the theatre tomorrow morning.','[\"going\", \"going to go\", \"am going to go\", \"are going to go\"]','are going to go','Future plan: Subject + be (present) + going to + verb.',4,'0c559ccd-2f8e-4644-b642-2f0cac112047'),('ca5de944-aacb-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','Jeremy studied a lot ________ successful in the History exam.','[\"being\", \"to be\", \"be\", \"to\"]','to be','Infinitive \"to be\" is used to show purpose.',4,'0c559ccd-2f8e-4644-b642-2f0cac112047'),('ca5df1f0-aacb-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','I started to work at a German company last month and my________is $2000 at this company.','[\"argument\", \"relax\", \"salary\", \"local\"]','salary','The correct word for monthly earnings is \"salary\".',4,'0c559ccd-2f8e-4644-b642-2f0cac112047'),('ca5df826-aacb-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','Adam is going to _______ about marketing at the company tomorrow.','[\"pay the bills\", \"take out the trash\", \"set the table\", \"give a presentation\"]','give a presentation','\"Give a presentation\" is the correct collocation for explaining something formally to an audience.',4,'0c559ccd-2f8e-4644-b642-2f0cac112047'),('ca5dfe0c-aacb-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','A: Hi, I want to go to Istanbul. Can I buy a bus ticket for tomorrow? B: One way or _________? A: One way. I don’t know when I will come back.','[\"direct bus\", \"gate\", \"round trip\", \"standard fare\"]','round trip','\"Round trip\" means going to a place and coming back.',4,'0c559ccd-2f8e-4644-b642-2f0cac112047'),('ca5e03a2-aacb-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','A: Hilary, when is your flight? B: My flight is at 17:00. _______ begins at 16:30.','[\"discount fare\", \"depart\", \"prior to\", \"boarding\"]','boarding','\"Boarding\" is the process of passengers getting onto the plane.',4,'0c559ccd-2f8e-4644-b642-2f0cac112047'),('ca5e08a2-aacb-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','Tyson likes eating ________ eggs at the breakfast. He wants to be a healthy person.','[\"steamed\", \"fried\", \"grilled\", \"baked\"]','steamed','\"Steamed\" eggs are cooked using steam, healthier option.',4,'0c559ccd-2f8e-4644-b642-2f0cac112047'),('ca5e0e60-aacb-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','A: Do you like watching comedies on TV? B: No, I prefer to watch _______. Beyaz Show is my favorite.','[\"sitcoms\", \"game shows\", \"talk shows\", \"sports shows\"]','sitcoms','\"Sitcoms\" are situational comedy shows on TV.',4,'0c559ccd-2f8e-4644-b642-2f0cac112047'),('d0c9e8e0-aaa9-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','A ________ prepares food at a restaurant.','[\"store clerk\", \"passenger\", \"server\", \"chef\"]','chef','A chef is a person who cooks food professionally in a restaurant.',1,'ca006437-6e09-4210-bebd-1538c9f53aac'),('d0ca08a2-aaa9-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','German is ______ than English.','[\"more difficult\", \"the most difficult\", \"difficult\", \"difficulty\"]','more difficult','Use “more + adjective” to compare two things: German is more difficult than English.',1,'ca006437-6e09-4210-bebd-1538c9f53aac'),('d0ca0ae6-aaa9-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','When ______ you born?','[\"are\", \"was\", \"were\", \"did\"]','were','We say “When were you born?” for past tense questions.',1,'ca006437-6e09-4210-bebd-1538c9f53aac'),('d461112c-8d85-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','Social experts advise that you should make _______ suggestions when people ask you to criticize their work.','[\"construct\",\"constructively\",\"construction\",\"constructive\"]','constructive','\"Doğru sıfat: constructive suggestions (yapıcı öneriler).\"',4,'356d75e5-4127-4e2c-8785-8d613234b516'),('d4614cb4-8d85-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','Shoplifters often work collaboratively, with one creating a diversion to _______ the shop assistants while the other steals the goods.','[\"distraction\",\"distracted\",\"distract\",\"distracting\"]','distract','\"Fiil gerekiyor: to distract the shop assistants (dikkatini dağıtmak).\"',4,'356d75e5-4127-4e2c-8785-8d613234b516'),('d4614fe8-8d85-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','Many of the deaths and illnesses which could have been foreseen and prevented in this region have arisen from _______ and the taking of unacceptable risks.','[\"ignorance\",\"ignore\",\"ignorant\",\"ignored\"]','ignorance','\"İsim formu gerekiyor: arisen from ignorance (cahillikten kaynaklanmak).\"',4,'356d75e5-4127-4e2c-8785-8d613234b516'),('d4615272-8d85-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','The happiest people do not _______ have the best of everything. They simply appreciate what they find on their way.','[\"necessity\",\"necessarily\",\"necessitate\",\"necessary\"]','necessarily','\"Doğru zarf: not necessarily (zorunlu olarak değil).\"',4,'356d75e5-4127-4e2c-8785-8d61