-b923-9ffbd079495d'),('e75f2c48-8e3c-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','You should pay the fee _______; otherwise, we will not accept your application.','[\"in advance\",\"same time\",\"subway\",\"insurance\"]','in advance','\"Önceden ödemek → pay in advance.\"',2,'19707430-e702-42b6-b923-9ffbd079495d'),('e75f2dce-8e3c-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','You must be very ____ in order to be a supermodel.','[\"better\",\"private\",\"similar\",\"slim\"]','slim','\"Supermodel olabilmek için → slim (zayıf, ince).\"',2,'19707430-e702-42b6-b923-9ffbd079495d'),('e8f0a844-aad8-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','Your sister and your brother are your _____.','[\"parents\", \"siblings\", \"cousins\", \"children\"]','siblings','\"Siblings\" kelimesi kardeş (erkek veya kız kardeş) anlamına gelir.',1,'cce5cff5-717d-4a4c-9d72-d554baa5e779'),('e8f12602-aad8-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','_______ names are Melanie and Jack.','[\"We\", \"Us\", \"Our\", \"Ours\"]','Our','\"Our\" bir iyelik sıfatıdır (bizim anlamına gelir). Cümlede isimden önce kullanılır: our names.',1,'cce5cff5-717d-4a4c-9d72-d554baa5e779'),('e8f12ada-aad8-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','He always eats lunch ______ twelve o`clock.','[\"in\", \"at\", \"on\", \"to\"]','at','\"At\" belirli saatlerle birlikte kullanılır. (at 12 o’clock = saat 12’de).',1,'cce5cff5-717d-4a4c-9d72-d554baa5e779'),('e8f1355c-aad8-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','My mother works in a hospital. ____ hospital is very big.','[\"The\", \"-\", \"A\", \"An\"]','The','Daha önce bahsedilen veya bilinen bir hastaneden söz edilirken \"The\" kullanılır.',1,'cce5cff5-717d-4a4c-9d72-d554baa5e779'),('e8f13e44-aad8-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','_________ do sports every day?','[\"You have to\", \"Do you have to\", \"Do you have\", \"Have you got\"]','Do you have to','“Do you have to” kalıbı bir zorunluluk veya alışkanlık hakkında soru sormak için kullanılır.',1,'cce5cff5-717d-4a4c-9d72-d554baa5e779'),('e8f14286-aad8-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','My sister loves Tim but he doesn`t love ______.','[\"his\", \"he\", \"her\", \"him\"]','her','\"Her\" kadınlar için kullanılan nesne zamiridir (onu anlamında).',1,'cce5cff5-717d-4a4c-9d72-d554baa5e779'),('e8f144d4-aad8-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','_______ a car? ---- No, I can`t.','[\"Can you drive\", \"You can drive\", \"Drive\", \"You drive\"]','Can you drive','Birinin bir şeyi yapabilme yeteneğini sormak için “Can you + fiil” yapısı kullanılır.',1,'cce5cff5-717d-4a4c-9d72-d554baa5e779'),('e8f147ea-aad8-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','She can`t ______ a computer.','[\"using\", \"to use\", \"use\", \"used\"]','use','\"Can\" yardımcı fiilinden sonra fiil yalın halde (use) kullanılır.',1,'cce5cff5-717d-4a4c-9d72-d554baa5e779'),('e8f14a10-aad8-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','________ trees in your garden.','[\"There are some\", \"Are there any\", \"Are there some\", \"Is there any\"]','There are some','“There are some” çoğul isimlerin varlığını belirtmek için kullanılır (bazı ağaçlar var).',1,'cce5cff5-717d-4a4c-9d72-d554baa5e779'),('e8f14c9a-aad8-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','There _____ magazines in the living room.','[\"are some\", \"is some\", \"are any\", \"is none\"]','are some','“Magazines” çoğul bir isimdir, bu yüzden “are some” doğru yapıdır (bazı dergiler var).',1,'cce5cff5-717d-4a4c-9d72-d554baa5e779'),('edb4bc60-ac74-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','Don’t leave your luggage ________. It looks suspicious.','[\"unattached\", \"unattractive\", \"unavoidable\", \"unattended\", \"unarmed\"]','unattended','“Luggage unattended” sabit kalıptır; güvenlik uyarılarında kullanılır.',3,'01697ee3-4023-4e80-9eaf-4b8b855bbe32'),('edb50e4a-ac74-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','We’re _________ in Spanish with my foreign friend who is living in Madrid now.','[\"relating\", \"connecting\", \"corresponding\", \"informing\", \"responding\"]','corresponding','“Correspond with someone” mektuplaşmak/iletişimde olmak anlamında resmî bir kullanımdır.',3,'01697ee3-4023-4e80-9eaf-4b8b855bbe32'),('edb56f02-ac74-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','Automated Teller Machines are a very convenient _________ of obtaining cash 24 hours a day.','[\"potential\", \"means\", \"skill\", \"arms\", \"property\"]','means','“A means of V‑ing” = bir şeyin yolu/vasıtası kalıbı.',3,'01697ee3-4023-4e80-9eaf-4b8b855bbe32'),('edb586e0-ac74-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','Thanks to the treatment Dr. Fitzgerald applied, Meg _________ recovered from her illness.','[\"fairly\", \"suitably\", \"lively\", \"punctually\", \"rapidly\"]','rapidly','İyileşme hızı anlatılır; “rapidly” en doğal zarftır.',3,'01697ee3-4023-4e80-9eaf-4b8b855bbe32'),('edb58e1a-ac74-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','You have to be at the airport one and two hours prior to domestic and international _________.','[\"obsessions\", \"eruptions\", \"excavations\", \"departures\", \"medications\"]','departures','Havaalanı terminolojisinde “departures” (kalkışlar) kullanılır.',3,'01697ee3-4023-4e80-9eaf-4b8b855bbe32'),('edb5928e-ac74-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','Some of the languages spoken in this area have a variety of _________ sounds.','[\"distinctive\", \"eternal\", \"fruitful\", \"premature\", \"deliberate\"]','distinctive','“Distinctive sounds” = ayırt edici sesler; akademik dilbilimde sık kullanılır.',3,'01697ee3-4023-4e80-9eaf-4b8b855bbe32'),('edb5954a-ac74-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','Had the regulations been _________ made, they wouldn’t have missed this opportunity.','[\"excessively\", \"disobediently\", \"inconveniently\", \"vertically\", \"adequately\"]','adequately','“Had + S + V3” ters şart yapısı; anlamca “yeterince” = adequately.',3,'01697ee3-4023-4e80-9eaf-4b8b855bbe32'),('edb59842-ac74-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','This receipt _________ that I bought these goods here on the day of my flight.','[\"experiments\", \"appreciates\", \"proves\", \"examines\", \"decreases\"]','proves','“Receipt proves …” = fiş kanıtlar kalıbı.',3,'01697ee3-4023-4e80-9eaf-4b8b855bbe32'),('edb59cb6-ac74-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','We _____ no problems whatsoever with the dam since it _____ forty years ago.','[\"had / has been constructed\", \"have had / was constructed\", \"had had / had been constructed\", \"are having / is constructed\", \"were having / was being constructed\"]','have had / was constructed','“Since + geçmiş referans” → günümüze kadar durum: present perfect; ikinci kısım simple past passive.',3,'01697ee3-4023-4e80-9eaf-4b8b855bbe32'),('edb5a058-ac74-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','Evaporation _____ the process by which a solid or liquid _____ into vapour by heat.','[\"is / changes\", \"is / is changed\", \"is / turns\", \"is / is turned\", \"is / has turned\"]','is / is turned','“Evaporation is the process by which … is turned into vapour by heat.” Pasif yapı uygundur.',3,'01697ee3-4023-4e80-9eaf-4b8b855bbe32'),('edb5a3b4-ac74-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','Leonardo da Vinci ______ a lot of paintings, but he _____ many of them.','[\"begins / couldn\'t finish\", \"began / didn\'t finish\", \"begun / finished\", \"was begin / didn\'t finish\", \"is beginning / couldn\'t finish\"]','began / didn\'t finish','İki eylem de geçmişte: “began” ve “didn’t finish” simple past.',3,'01697ee3-4023-4e80-9eaf-4b8b855bbe32'),('f44afb4e-8e96-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','Marta _____ from terrible back ache lately, because she _____ to work in a shop that she has to carry heavy things last month.','[\"has suffered/is starting\",\"was suffering/starts\",\"is suffering/has started\",\"suffers/was starting\",\"has been suffering/started\"]','has been suffering/started','\"Present Perfect Continuous + Past Simple: She has been suffering (devam eden durum) because she started (geçmişte olan olay).\"',3,'d475b5bf-9c5e-4b8f-a462-40a9e5132dd1'),('f44b3a82-8e96-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','As my father _____ in a house next to a highway, he barely _____ disturbed by truck noises when we stayed at the hotel.','[\"used to bring up / gets\",\"was brought up / will get\",\"had been brought up / got\",\"had brought up / was getting\",\"brought up / is getting\"]','had been brought up / got','\"Past Perfect Passive + Past Simple: He had been brought up (önceki süreç) → he got disturbed (o an yaşanan olay).\"',3,'d475b5bf-9c5e-4b8f-a462-40a9e5132dd1'),('f44b3f50-8e96-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','I think Jessy _____ her holiday abroad if she _____ with others but she is so shy.','[\"enjoyed/had been socializing\",\"could have enjoyed/has socialised\",\"had enjoyed/was socialising\",\"enjoys/will have socialised\",\"would enjoy/socialized\"]','would enjoy/socialized','\"Type 2 Conditional: Jessy would enjoy if she socialized (gerçek dışı durum – shy olduğu için yapmıyor).\"',3,'d475b5bf-9c5e-4b8f-a462-40a9e5132dd1'),('f44b4572-8e96-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','No one can change her mind if she has already decided to leave, _____?','[\"hasn’t she\",\"can’t they\",\"has she\",\"can they\",\"can\"]','can they','\"Question tag: No one → they (olumsuzdan sonra olumlu gelir). Correct: can they?\"',3,'d475b5bf-9c5e-4b8f-a462-40a9e5132dd1'),('f4e947b8-aaa7-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','Please don’t smoke ____ the car. The seats smell cigarette.','[\"behind\", \"in front of\", \"under\", \"in\"]','in','We say \"in the car\" because it is an enclosed space. Use \"in\" for cars, rooms, buildings.',2,'21aed928-0900-4c67-b32a-8068e3ec8959'),('f4ea095a-aaa7-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','_________ cola very much. It’s not delicious.','[\"I don’t eat\", \"I like\", \"I drink\", \"I don’t like\"]','I don’t like','We use \"don’t like\" to express dislike. The correct verb is \"like\", not \"eat\" or \"drink\" here.',2,'21aed928-0900-4c67-b32a-8068e3ec8959'),('f4ea0cd4-aaa7-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','Roby: ____________________? Mily: Yes, I do.','[\"Does Linda go swimming\", \"Do I play this game correctly\", \"Do you do aerobics\", \"Do you and your brother watch TV\"]','Do you do aerobics','The answer \"Yes, I do\" shows the question is in simple present tense and about \"you\".',2,'21aed928-0900-4c67-b32a-8068e3ec8959'),('f4ea0f4a-aaa7-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','Jack: Do students play basketball in the school team? Terry: __________________. We don’t have a basketball team.','[\"Yes, they play\", \"No, they aren’t\", \"Yes, I do\", \"No, they don’t\"]','No, they don’t','Use \"do/does\" for simple present questions and answers. Negative answer: \"No, they don’t.\"',2,'21aed928-0900-4c67-b32a-8068e3ec8959'),('f4ea11b6-aaa7-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','Alice: ___________ to school? Betty: I study at Oxford University.','[\"How does Nancy go\", \"What do we study\", \"What time do you leave\", \"Where do you go\"]','Where do you go','The answer \"I study at Oxford University\" answers a \"Where\" question about location.',2,'21aed928-0900-4c67-b32a-8068e3ec8959'),('f4ea13dc-aaa7-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','William: What do you eat for lunch? Carl: ______________.','[\"At 12 o’clock\", \"In the cafeteria\", \"A sandwich\", \"A glass of milk\"]','A sandwich','The question \"What do you eat?\" asks for food. Correct type of answer: food item, not time or place.',2,'21aed928-0900-4c67-b32a-8068e3ec8959'),('f4ea1dfa-aaa7-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','Ellie: How often do you go to cinema? Robert: ______________.','[\"Once a month\", \"Yes, I do\", \"In the city center\", \"No, I don’t\"]','Once a month','\"How often\" questions ask for frequency. Use expressions like \"once/twice a week/month\".',2,'21aed928-0900-4c67-b32a-8068e3ec8959'),('f4ea1f58-aaa7-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','William: Hello. I’m William Moore. Katy: __________________? William: It’s M – double O – R – E.','[\"Nice to meet you\", \"My name is Katy\", \"How do you spell that\", \"What is your name\"]','How do you spell that','The answer \"It’s M-double O-R-E\" shows the question asks about spelling.',2,'21aed928-0900-4c67-b32a-8068e3ec8959'),('f4ea2106-aaa7-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','Abraham: Hi, my name is Abraham. Jacob: Hey, I’m Jacob. ___________. Abraham: Thanks. Pleased to meet you, too.','[\"What’s your name\", \"How old are you\", \"I’m fine\", \"Nice to meet you\"]','Nice to meet you','Greeting exchange pattern: \"Nice to meet you\" → \"Pleased to meet you, too.\"',2,'21aed928-0900-4c67-b32a-8068e3ec8959'),('f4ea285e-aaa7-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','Matthew: Hi, Barbara. How are you? Barbara: I’m fine, thanks. ________? Matthew: Fine.','[\"I’m not bad\", \"Where is she from\", \"And you\", \"Are you sad\"]','And you','Typical conversation: \"How are you?\" → \"I’m fine, thanks. And you?\"',2,'21aed928-0900-4c67-b32a-8068e3ec8959'),('f71acd26-abbb-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','Right now, Sarah ______ (work) on a very important project that she ______ (not finish) yet, but she hopes to complete it by tomorrow.','[\"works / hadn’t finished\", \"is working / hasn’t finished\", \"has worked / didn’t finish\", \"worked / doesn’t finish\"]','is working / hasn’t finished','\"Right now\" şimdiki zamanı gösterir → “is working”. “Yet” ile olumsuz cümlede present perfect kullanılır → “hasn’t finished”.',3,'0de5fd2d-555f-4ba1-bccb-450b8df2f817'),('f71b3da6-abbb-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','While I ______ (walk) to the bus stop yesterday, I ______ (see) an old friend I hadn’t seen in years.','[\"walked / have seen\", \"was walking / saw\", \"have walked / had seen\", \"am walking / will see\"]','was walking / saw','“While” geçmişte devam eden bir olayı anlatır → “was walking”. O anda gerçekleşen kısa olay → “saw”.',3,'0de5fd2d-555f-4ba1-bccb-450b8df2f817'),('f71b4152-abbb-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','He didn’t run fast ________ to catch the bus, and now he ________ for the next one.','[\"too/ has waited\", \"enough/ has to wait\", \"not enough/ waited\", \"so/ waits\"]','enough/ has to wait','“Fast enough” = yeterince hızlı. “Has to wait” = beklemek zorunda.',3,'0de5fd2d-555f-4ba1-bccb-450b8df2f817'),('f71b4422-abbb-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','This is ______ cake I’ve ever tasted—it’s even ______ than the one my grandmother makes!','[\"the most delicious / better\", \"the more delicious / best\", \"more delicious / good\", \"most delicious / well\"]','the most delicious / better','“The most delicious” → üstünlük derecesi (superlative). “Better” → iki şey karşılaştırıldığında kullanılır.',3,'0de5fd2d-555f-4ba1-bccb-450b8df2f817'),('f71b4670-abbb-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','They have been friends ______ they were in primary school, and they have always supported each other through difficult times.','[\"for\", \"just\", \"already\", \"since\"]','since','“Since” → bir başlangıç zamanını belirtir. “They have been friends since primary school.”',3,'0de5fd2d-555f-4ba1-bccb-450b8df2f817'),('f71b48d2-abbb-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','I don\'t mind __________ (work) late, but I hate missing my favorite TV show.','[\"to work\", \"working\", \"to working\", \"work\"]','working','“Mind” fiilinden sonra her zaman “-ing” gelir → “don’t mind working”.',3,'0de5fd2d-555f-4ba1-bccb-450b8df2f817'),('f71b4ae4-abbb-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','He can\'t afford to buy a new car yet, but he’s looking forward to __________ (find) a good deal.','[\"to find\", \"find\", \"to finding\", \"finding\"]','finding','“Look forward to” kalıbından sonra her zaman “-ing” gelir → “looking forward to finding”.',3,'0de5fd2d-555f-4ba1-bccb-450b8df2f817'),('f71b4cba-abbb-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','When I was younger, I ______ (play) soccer every afternoon with my friends in the park, but now I ______ (not have) enough time for it.','[\"used to play / don’t have\", \"had played / am not having\", \"was played / didn’t have\", \"use to play / haven’t had\"]','used to play / don’t have','“Used to” geçmişte alışkanlıkları anlatır. Şimdi geçerli değil. → “don’t have” ile devam eder.',3,'0de5fd2d-555f-4ba1-bccb-450b8df2f817'),('f71b5ad4-abbb-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','The restaurant ______ we had dinner last night was amazing—the food was delicious, the service was excellent, and the atmosphere was perfect.','[\"who\", \"which\", \"where\", \"when\"]','where','Yer bildirimi için “where” kullanılır → “The restaurant where we had dinner…”',3,'0de5fd2d-555f-4ba1-bccb-450b8df2f817'),('f71b5cd2-abbb-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','The problem with that house is that it’s not spacious __________ and it’s __________ expensive.','[\"enough / too\", \"too / enough\", \"so / such\", \"very / such\"]','enough / too','“Not spacious enough” = yeterince geniş değil. “Too expensive” = çok pahalı.',3,'0de5fd2d-555f-4ba1-bccb-450b8df2f817'),('f748821e-ac7b-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','She enjoys reading a good __________ before going to bed.','[\"movie\", \"book\", \"song\", \"game\", \"sport\"]','book','“reading a good book” doğal kalıptır.',1,'00a862d7-735d-4c17-bbaf-5d6889aa2bd8'),('f748ecfe-ac7b-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','He spoke __________ during the meeting, ensuring everyone understood the instructions.','[\"clearly\", \"softly\", \"hastily\", \"confidently\", \"quietly\"]','clearly','Anlaşılır olmayı vurgular: “spoke clearly”.',1,'00a862d7-735d-4c17-bbaf-5d6889aa2bd8'),('f748f05a-ac7b-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','I usually __________ to work, but today I\'m __________ the bus because my car is in the shop.','[\"walk / am taking\", \"walked / take\", \"walking / took\", \"walks / taking\", \"walking / to take\"]','walk / am taking','Alışkanlık için simple present, geçici durum için present continuous kullanılır.',1,'00a862d7-735d-4c17-bbaf-5d6889aa2bd8'),('f748fa32-ac7b-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','She was hungry, __________ she decided to grab a snack before dinner.','[\"or\", \"yet\", \"so\", \"because\", \"while\"]','so','Neden-sonuçta “so” uygun: açtı, bu yüzden atıştırdı.',1,'00a862d7-735d-4c17-bbaf-5d6889aa2bd8'),('f748fcee-ac7b-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','I had to postpone my trip to Australia last week________.','[\"as I have lost my passport\", \"since the airline employees are on strike\", \"due to bad weather conditions\", \"for my wife has a traffic accident\", \"if I had known that you lost your mother\"]','due to bad weather conditions','“due to + isim” neden belirtir ve “last week” ile uyumlu.',1,'00a862d7-735d-4c17-bbaf-5d6889aa2bd8'),('f7490068-ac7b-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','By the time the doctor came in to examine my daughter, ________.','[\"she has been suffering from headache for three hours\", \"I will try to keep her calm as she is afraid of dentists\", \"the nurse has already injected her the vaccine\", \"her temperature had risen to 40 centigrade\", \"I will have to wait outside\"]','her temperature had risen to 40 centigrade','“By the time + past” → önce gerçekleşen olay past perfect olur.',1,'00a862d7-735d-4c17-bbaf-5d6889aa2bd8'),('f7490ba8-ac7b-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','You are at a restaurant and want to order something vegetarian. How would you ask the waiter for recommendations?','[\"Can you suggest anything on the menu?\", \"Do you have any meat dishes?\", \"I would like something without meat, what do you recommend?\", \"Are there any soft drinks available?\", \"Could you help me order something?\"]','I would like something without meat, what do you recommend?','Vejetaryen tercihi açıkça belirtir ve öneri ister.',1,'00a862d7-735d-4c17-bbaf-5d6889aa2bd8'),('f7490ebe-ac7b-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','Emily: Did you enjoy the concert last night? Tom: __________. The band played all my favorite songs.','[\"No, I didn\'t like it at all.\", \"I haven\'t been to a concert in years.\", \"Yes, it was amazing.\", \"I prefer classical music.\", \"I don\'t go to concerts.\"]','Yes, it was amazing.','Olumlu takip cümlesiyle uyumlu doğal yanıt.',1,'00a862d7-735d-4c17-bbaf-5d6889aa2bd8'),('f74929ee-ac7b-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','We need some help. I wish my brother __________ here now.','[\"will be\", \"were\", \"have been\", \"can be\", \"is\"]','were','Unreal present “wish” yapısında tüm öznelerle “were” kullanılır.',1,'00a862d7-735d-4c17-bbaf-5d6889aa2bd8'),('f7492f66-ac7b-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','I’ll go swimming tomorrow __________ it\'s cold.','[\"in case\", \"if\", \"unless\", \"as if\", \"even if\"]','even if','“Even if” = olsa bile; soğuğa rağmen gitme niyeti.',1,'00a862d7-735d-4c17-bbaf-5d6889aa2bd8'),('f749336c-ac7b-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','If I __________ breakfast in the morning, I __________ hungry now.','[\"ate / wasn\'t\", \"had eaten / wouldn\'t have been\", \"eat / can\'t be\", \"ate / wouldn\'t be\", \"had eaten / wouldn\'t be\"]','had eaten / wouldn\'t be','Geçmişte (sabah) gerçekleşmeyen eylemin bugüne etkisi: mixed conditional.',1,'00a862d7-735d-4c17-bbaf-5d6889aa2bd8'),('f7493772-ac7b-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','________ those days, ________ the 1990s computers weren’t used so much in my country.','[\"In / in\", \"On / in\", \"During / on\", \"At / on\", \"On / at\"]','In / in','Zaman zarflarıyla doğal kullanım: “in those days / in the 1990s”.',1,'00a862d7-735d-4c17-bbaf-5d6889aa2bd8'),('f7493a92-ac7b-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','The efforts of humanity to find the truth __________ trial and error have broadened the boundaries __________ science.','[\"through / of\", \"by / at\", \"with / for\", \"via / to\", \"during / from\"]','through / of','Doğal kalıp: “through trial and error” ve “boundaries of science”.',1,'00a862d7-735d-4c17-bbaf-5d6889aa2bd8'),('f7b7b5ca-8a53-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','My husband is from ............ .','[\"Italian\",\"Japan\",\"Spanish\",\"Russian\"]','Japan','from + ülke adı kullanılır. Italian/Spanish/Russian sıfat; “from Japan” doğrudur.',1,'8b412a01-bc73-48da-adef-2c6e6d92a00a'),('f7b8ed00-8a53-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','We have PE classes ............. Mondays.','[\"in\",\"at\",\"on\",\"from\"]','on','Gün isimleriyle “on” kullanılır: on Mondays.',1,'8b412a01-bc73-48da-adef-2c6e6d92a00a'),('f7b8f1ba-8a53-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','I haven’t got ........... car.','[\"the\",\"a\",\"an\",\"-\"]','a','Tekil sayılabilir isim ilk kez geçiyorsa “a” gelir: a car.',1,'8b412a01-bc73-48da-adef-2c6e6d92a00a'),('f7b8fc1e-8a53-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','........... book over there is mine.','[\"That\",\"This\",\"Those\",\"These\"]','That','Uzak nesne için “that”; “over there” uzaklığı gösterir.',1,'8b412a01-bc73-48da-adef-2c6e6d92a00a'),('f7b8fe80-8a53-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','My sister has two sons. They are my ............... .','[\"nephews\",\"children\",\"cousins\",\"nieces\"]','nephews','Kız kardeşinin erkek çocukları: nephew(s).',1,'8b412a01-bc73-48da-adef-2c6e6d92a00a'),('f7b90894-8a53-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','9:45 is .................... .','[\"half past nine\",\"quarter past nine\",\"quarter to nine\",\"quarter to ten\"]','quarter to ten','9:45 → 10’a çeyrek kala: quarter to ten.',1,'8b412a01-bc73-48da-adef-2c6e6d92a00a'),('f7b912c6-8a53-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','............. are three computers in the office.','[\"They\",\"There\",\"We\",\"You\"]','There','Var-yok cümleleri “There is/are” ile kurulur.',1,'8b412a01-bc73-48da-adef-2c6e6d92a00a'),('f7b913e8-8a53-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','My mother .............. long blonde hair.','[\"is\",\"are\",\"has got\",\"does\"]','has got','Sahiplik için “has got/has” kullanılır: has got long hair.',1,'8b412a01-bc73-48da-adef-2c6e6d92a00a'),('f7b91500-8a53-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','John is a lawyer. ........... office is in London.','[\"His\",\"Him\",\"He\",\"Their\"]','His','İyelik sıfatı: his office.',1,'8b412a01-bc73-48da-adef-2c6e6d92a00a'),('f7b916a4-8a53-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','She has ........................... .','[\"a house small\",\"small a house\",\"a small house\",\"small house\"]','a small house','Sıra: article + adjective + noun → a small house.',1,'8b412a01-bc73-48da-adef-2c6e6d92a00a'),('f93427ee-ac72-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','With his great style, Messi quickly became a world-famous football star. Today, football fans all around the world ____________ that he is the present-day Maradona.','[\"think\", \"are thinking\", \"has been thinking\", \"thought\"]','think','\"All around the world\" genel bir durumu belirtir; bu yüzden simple present tense (think) doğru seçenektir.',4,'05e48369-5ea9-4ef0-ab6f-9f5d29358929'),('f934e35a-ac72-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','Because there was a huge rainstorm, the flight ___________ for more than an hour. The airport was full of angry passengers.','[\"delayed\", \"is delayed\", \"delays\", \"was delayed\"]','was delayed','Geçmişte tamamlanmış bir olayı anlatır; bu yüzden past simple (was delayed) doğru cevaptır.',4,'05e48369-5ea9-4ef0-ab6f-9f5d29358929'),('f934e7ce-ac72-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','Since the Industrial Revolution of the 19th century, human activities ____________ the Earth’s ecological balance significantly.','[\"has damaged\", \"have been damaging\", \"damaged\", \"are being damaging\"]','have been damaging','\"Since\" ifadesi geçmişten bugüne süregelen bir durumu anlatır; present perfect continuous (have been damaging) doğru seçenektir.',4,'05e48369-5ea9-4ef0-ab6f-9f5d29358929'),('f9350d94-ac72-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','I am taking Spanish classes at the community college because I _________________ in Barcelona next spring and I thought knowing a little Spanish would make me feel more comfortable.','[\"am going to study\", \"have been studying\", \"will study\", \"have studied\"]','am going to study','\"Next spring\" geleceğe yöneliktir; planlı bir eylem olduğu için \'am going to study\' doğru seçenektir.',4,'05e48369-5ea9-4ef0-ab6f-9f5d29358929'),('f93511ea-ac72-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','Before the legislation made last year, smoking ____________________ in closed areas in the whole country.','[\"is allowed\", \"did allowed\", \"was allowed\", \"had allowed\"]','was allowed','Geçmişte geçerli olan bir durum anlatılır; past simple passive (was allowed) doğru seçenektir.',4,'05e48369-5ea9-4ef0-ab6f-9f5d29358929'),('f93514c4-ac72-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','Recently, a survey was carried out in order to determine the good and the bad drivers: Young, old, male and female. Which ones are ________________ of all?','[\"the safer\", \"safest\", \"the most safest\", \"the safest\"]','the safest','Superlative yapılarda “the + adjective + est” kullanılır; “the safest” doğrudur.',4,'05e48369-5ea9-4ef0-ab6f-9f5d29358929'),('f93517c6-ac72-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','Children are exposed to many advertisements for unhealthy foods, ______________ parents must educate their children about good food and nutrition.','[\"because\", \"therefore\", \"since\", \"whereas\"]','therefore','İlk cümle neden, ikinci cümle sonuç bildiriyor; bu nedenle bağlaç “therefore” doğru seçenektir.',4,'05e48369-5ea9-4ef0-ab6f-9f5d29358929'),('f93519c4-ac72-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','A: Do you know where Pedro is? I have been calling his office for almost an hour, but no answer. Isn’t he working today? B: You know he only skips work for important events, and today is the final game of the World Cup. He ____________________ at a bar watching the game.','[\"must be\", \"should be\", \"might be\", \"can be\"]','must be','Yüksek olasılık ifade edilir; bu durumda “must be” en uygun seçenektir.',4,'05e48369-5ea9-4ef0-ab6f-9f5d29358929'),('f9352da6-ac72-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','The teacher wanted to know ________________________.','[\"why students hadn’t done their assignment on Geography\", \"how could students prevent themselves from wasting time\", \"whether did students understand the topic of reported questions in English\", \"what is the best method to write an effective essay\"]','why students hadn’t done their assignment on Geography','“Wanted to know” ifadesinden sonra dolaylı soru gelir; bu yüzden “why students hadn’t done …” doğru yapıdır.',4,'05e48369-5ea9-4ef0-ab6f-9f5d29358929'),('f9353292-ac72-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','Anne continued knocking the door hard _____________ she knew quite well that this was the only way to wake her husband up.','[\"although\", \"while\", \"because\", \"but\"]','because','“Only way” ifadesi nedeni belirtir; bu yüzden “because” doğru seçenektir.',4,'05e48369-5ea9-4ef0-ab6f-9f5d29358929'),('f96872ce-8b2a-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','She usually ........ to school by bus, but today she ........ on foot.','[\"goes / is walking\",\"go / walks\",\"going / walked\",\"goes / walk\"]','goes / is walking','Rutin için Present Simple: goes; şu an olan durum için Present Continuous: is walking.',1,'8b412a01-bc73-48da-adef-2c6e6d92a00a'),('f96891f0-8b2a-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','24. There ........ a book and two pens on the desk.','[\"is\",\"are\",\"was\",\"were\"]','are','“two pens” çoğul olduğu için “are” kullanılır.',1,'8b412a01-bc73-48da-adef-2c6e6d92a00a'),('ff639de2-aaa7-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','Isaac: _________________________? Abraham: Yes. There is a chemist’s in New Street. That’s the second street on the left. Isaac: Thanks.','[\"Where can I find the chemist’s in New Street\", \"Is the second street on the left King Street\", \"Excuse me. Is there a chemist’s near here, please\", \"Sorry. Is there a school around here\"]','Excuse me. Is there a chemist’s near here, please','Polite question to ask for locations: \"Is there a ... near here, please?\"',2,'21aed928-0900-4c67-b32a-8068e3ec8959'),('ff640750-aaa7-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','Jane: What is this? Betty: This is ____ umbrella.','[\"a\", \"the\", \"an\", \"two\"]','an','We use \"an\" before vowel sounds like umbrella (u-).',2,'21aed928-0900-4c67-b32a-8068e3ec8959'),('ff6412ae-aaa7-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','____ son is a male child.','[\"A\", \"The\", \"An\", \"Two\"]','A','We use \"A\" for general definitions (A son = one example of male child).',2,'21aed928-0900-4c67-b32a-8068e3ec8959'),('ff64148e-aaa7-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','Hello! I’m Kate and this is my sister. ____ name is Angelina.','[\"His\", \"Your\", \"Her\", \"Their\"]','Her','Possessive adjective for female: her = belonging to a girl/woman.',2,'21aed928-0900-4c67-b32a-8068e3ec8959'),('ff6416fa-aaa7-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','John: Is this your school? Gabriel: No, it isn’t. ____ school is in the Brooklyn Street.','[\"My\", \"Your\", \"Its\", \"Her\"]','My','Possessive adjective: \"my school\" means the school that belongs to me.',2,'21aed928-0900-4c67-b32a-8068e3ec8959'),('ff6421ea-aaa7-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','Jennifer and Brian ____ from the USA.','[\"am\", \"are\", \"is\", \"be\"]','are','Subject is plural (Jennifer and Brian) → use \"are\".',2,'21aed928-0900-4c67-b32a-8068e3ec8959'),('ff64238e-aaa7-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','Robin: ______ married? Barbara: No, she isn’t.','[\"Lily is\", \"Are you\", \"David is\", \"Is your sister\"]','Is your sister','Question about a third person singular uses \"Is\" + subject.',2,'21aed928-0900-4c67-b32a-8068e3ec8959'),('ff642500-aaa7-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','Carla: Are you a student? Phillip: _______.','[\"Yes, I’m.\", \"No, they aren’t\", \"No, he is not.\", \"Yes, he is.\"]','Yes, I’m.','Correct short answer: \"Yes, I am.\" (informal contraction \"I’m\" is acceptable).',2,'21aed928-0900-4c67-b32a-8068e3ec8959'),('ff642d98-aaa7-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','There ____ two dogs in the garden.','[\"is\", \"are\", \"am\", \"be\"]','are','Use \"are\" for plural countable nouns: there are two dogs.',2,'21aed928-0900-4c67-b32a-8068e3ec8959'),('ff642ef6-aaa7-11f0-a718-e9d776cb9790','Look! The children ____ playing football.','[\"is\", \"are\", \"am\", \"be\"]','are','Present continuous with plural subject: are + V-ing.',2,'21aed928-0900-4c67-b32a-8068e3ec8959');
