ents and NGOs often support urban gardening projects with workshops and resources. Knowledge sharing and collaboration among residents improve success rates.','B2','2025-09-18 18:11:37.000'),('c5857800-94a1-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','B2 – Renewable Transportation','Electric vehicles (EVs) are becoming common worldwide. EVs reduce greenhouse gas emissions and dependence on fossil fuels. Charging infrastructure, battery life, and cost remain challenges. Governments incentivize EV adoption through subsidies and tax benefits. Consumers are encouraged to research models, plan charging routes, and adopt eco-friendly habits. The transition to renewable transportation is essential for sustainable cities and a cleaner environment.','B2','2025-09-18 18:11:37.000'),('c585ca6c-94a1-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','B2 – Digital Privacy','Digital privacy has become a critical concern in the modern world. Personal data is collected by apps, websites, and social media platforms. Users often unknowingly share sensitive information that can be misused. Cybersecurity measures, strong passwords, and cautious online behavior are essential. Governments and companies are introducing regulations to protect user data. Awareness and education are key to ensuring individuals can safeguard their privacy effectively.','B2','2025-09-18 18:11:37.000'),('c58607ca-94a1-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','B2 – Space Tourism','Space tourism is emerging as a new industry, offering civilians the opportunity to travel beyond Earth. Companies are developing spacecraft that can carry private passengers safely. Despite excitement, high costs and safety concerns are challenges. Space tourism also raises ethical questions regarding environmental impact and accessibility. Researchers study the effects of space travel on human physiology to ensure safety. If successful, space tourism could inspire interest in science and technology among the general public.','B2','2025-09-18 18:11:37.000'),('cdd92b54-949d-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','