th. She attends online classes three times a week and practices vocabulary every day. She also watches French movies with subtitles and listens to French songs. Learning a new language is challenging but enjoyable. She hopes to travel to France next year to use her skills in real situations.','B1','2025-09-18 17:43:24.000'),('dc1fd372-94cd-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','A2 – Visiting a Zoo','Last Saturday, I went to the zoo with my family. We saw lions, elephants, and monkeys. I took many photos and fed some animals under supervision. There was also a small aquarium with colorful fish. We spent the whole afternoon there and had ice cream before leaving.','A2','2025-09-18 23:27:13.000'),('dc208c0e-94cd-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','A2 – Baking a Cake','Yesterday, I baked a chocolate cake for my mother\'s birthday. I measured all the ingredients carefully and mixed them. The cake baked in the oven for 40 minutes. I decorated it with chocolate and strawberries. My family loved the cake and said it was delicious.','A2','2025-09-18 23:27:13.000'),('dc20c17e-94cd-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','A2 – Going to the Beach','Last summer, I went to the beach with my friends. We swam in the sea and played volleyball on the sand. I built a sandcastle with my little cousin. We had ice cream and cold drinks under the sun. It was a very fun and sunny day.','A2','2025-09-18 23:27:13.000'),('dc20f27a-94cd-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','A2 – A Visit to the Museum','Yesterday, I went to the city museum with my class. We saw paintings, sculptures, and historical artifacts. Our guide explained the history of each exhibit. I took some photos to remember the visit. I learned a lot about the city\'s history and culture.','A2','2025-09-18 23:27:13.000'),('dc213d5c-94cd-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','A2 – Shopping for Groceries','Last Saturday, I went shopping for groceries. I bought vegetables, fruits, bread, and milk. The supermarket was busy and had many people. I paid at the cashier and packed my bags. On my way home, I met my neighbor and we talked about our plans for the weekend.','A2','2025-09-18 23:27:13.000'),('e06d0f2c-94cc-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','A1 – Going to the Library','Yesterday, I went to the library with my friend. We borrowed some books about animals and history. The library was quiet and full of shelves. We read for one hour and then returned the books. It was a peaceful afternoon.','A1','2025-09-18 23:20:10.000'),('e06d8e70-94cc-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','A1 – Cleaning the Room','This morning, I cleaned my room. I put the clothes in the wardrobe and books on the shelf. I also vacuumed the floor and opened the windows. My room looks neat and tidy now. I feel proud of my work.','A1','2025-09-18 23:20:10.000'),('e06dd164-94cc-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','A1 – A Picnic','Last Sunday, my family went on a picnic to the river. We took sandwiches, juice, and fruits. The sun was shining and the birds were singing. We played games and took photos. It was a relaxing day in nature.','A1','2025-09-18 23:20:10.000'),('e06e1a02-94cc-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','A1 – Visiting Grandparents','Yesterday, I visited my grandparents. We drank tea and ate cookies together. My grandfather told me stories from his childhood. I helped my grandmother in the garden. I love spending time with them.','A1','2025-09-18 23:20:10.000'),('e06e6c50-94cc-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','A1 – Riding a Bicycle','In the morning, I rode my bicycle in the park. I wore a helmet for safety. I rode fast and enjoyed the fresh air. I saw children playing and dogs running around. After an hour, I returned home feeling happy.','A1','2025-09-18 23:20:10.000'),('ee19ae94-94a1-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','B2 – Smart Cities','Smart cities integrate technology to improve urban living. Sensors, data analysis, and connected devices help manage traffic, energy, and waste efficiently. Citizens can access real-time information about public transport and services. While technology improves convenience, privacy and cybersecurity concerns must be addressed. Collaborative governance and citizen engagement are essential for success. Long-term planning and sustainable development guide smart city initiatives.','B2','2025-09-18 18:12:45.000'),('ee1b7c88-94a1-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','B2 – Ocean Pollution','Oceans are facing severe pollution due to plastic waste, oil spills, and chemical runoff. Marine life suffers from ingestion of plastics, entanglement, and habitat loss. Humans are also affected as seafood can contain microplastics and toxins. Governments, NGOs, and citizens must cooperate to reduce pollution by implementing stricter regulations, cleaning programs, and raising awareness. Education and sustainable consumption habits play a crucial role in mitigating ocean pollution.','B2','2025-09-18 18:12:45.000'),('ee1bd912-94a1-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','B2 – Global Health Challenges','Global health challenges include pandemics, malnutrition, and access to clean water. International organizations coordinate responses to outbreaks and support healthcare systems in vulnerable regions. Vaccination campaigns and preventive measures save millions of lives yearly. Despite progress, inequalities in healthcare access remain a significant concern. Research, funding, and education are necessary to tackle these challenges effectively. Individuals can contribute by promoting hygiene, vaccination, and healthy lifestyles.','B2','2025-09-18 18:12:45.000'),('ee1bfb90-94a1-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','B2 – Renewable Energy Innovations','Innovations in renewable energy include solar panels, wind turbines, and bioenergy solutions. Engineers develop more efficient and affordable technologies to replace fossil fuels. Governments fund research and provide incentives for businesses and households adopting renewable systems. Community projects and education programs raise awareness and encourage participation. Challenges remain, such as storage, intermittency, and initial costs. Global cooperation accelerates progress towards sustainable energy futures.','B2','2025-09-18 18:12:45.000'),('ee1c1bde-94a1-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','B2 – Artificial Intelligence Ethics','The rapid growth of AI technologies raises ethical questions. Issues include data privacy, algorithmic bias, job displacement, and decision-making transparency. Companies and governments are creating policies to ensure responsible AI use. Educating developers, policymakers, and the public about ethical AI practices is crucial. Continuous monitoring and feedback help mitigate unintended consequences. Ethical AI fosters trust, accountability, and long-term societal benefit.','B2','2025-09-18 18:12:45.000'),('ee1c3998-94a1-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','B2 – Space Debris','Space debris consists of defunct satellites, rocket stages, and fragments from collisions. It poses serious risks to operational spacecraft and astronauts. Tracking and removing debris is a major challenge for space agencies. International cooperation, advanced technology, and strict regulations are required to minimize collisions. Public awareness and research on debris management strategies are essential. Addressing space debris ensures safer space exploration for future generations.','B2','2025-09-18 18:12:45.000'),('ef3fb41e-9490-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','A1 – My Family','I live with my family in a small house. My mother cooks dinner every evening. My father likes reading books. I have one sister and one brother. We all watch TV together after dinner.','A1','2025-09-18 16:11:05.862'),('ef40543c-9490-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','A1 – At School','My name is John. I am ten years old. I go to school from Monday to Friday. My favorite subject is English. At school, I play football with my friends during the break. After school, I do my homework and then read a book.','A1','2025-09-18 16:11:05.865'),('f4086660-94ce-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','A2 – A Trip to the Mountains','Last weekend, I went to the mountains with my family. We hiked for two hours and enjoyed the fresh air. I took many photos of the beautiful scenery. We had a picnic near a small river and watched the birds. In the evening, we returned home tired but happy.','A2','2025-09-18 23:35:02.000'),('f409279e-94ce-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','A2 – Visiting a Science Museum','Yesterday, I went to a science museum with my classmates. We saw many experiments and learned about electricity and magnets. I tried a small experiment about static electricity. We also watched a short film about space. I enjoyed learning new things and asking questions.','A2','2025-09-18 23:35:02.000'),('f40a0a9c-94ce-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','A2 – Gardening at Home','This weekend, I helped my mother in the garden. We planted flowers and watered the vegetables. I learned how to take care of plants. Some butterflies came and we watched them for a while. Gardening is relaxing and fun, and I felt proud of our work.','A2','2025-09-18 23:35:02.000'),('f40a597a-94ce-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','A2 – A Visit to the Art Gallery','Last Friday, I visited an art gallery with my class. We saw paintings, sculptures, and photographs. I liked the colorful paintings the most. The guide explained the artists and their techniques. I asked some questions about the artworks. The visit helped me understand more about art.','A2','2025-09-18 23:35:02.000'),('f6c44e64-94c9-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','B2 – The Rise of Artificial Intelligence','Artificial Intelligence (AI) has become an essential part of modern society. From self-driving cars to medical diagnoses, AI is transforming industries. While it offers incredible opportunities for progress, it also raises ethical questions. Many fear that automation may replace human jobs, while others believe it will create new roles that never existed before. Governments and companies are now discussing how to regulate AI in a way that ensures safety, fairness, and innovation.','B2','2025-09-18 22:59:19.000'),('f6c8a464-94c9-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','B2 – Climate Change and Global Action','Climate change is one of the greatest challenges humanity faces today. Rising global temperatures have led to extreme weather events such as hurricanes, floods, and droughts. Scientists agree that human activities, especially burning fossil fuels, are the main cause. International organizations urge countries to reduce carbon emissions and invest in renewable energy sources. Public awareness campaigns also play an important role, as individual actions like recycling and saving energy contribute to the fight against climate change.','B2','2025-09-18 22:59:19.000'),('f6e79fcc-94c9-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','B2 – The Importance of Cultural Diversity','Cultural diversity enriches societies by bringing different traditions, languages, and perspectives together. It allows people to learn from one another and develop tolerance and respect. In workplaces, diverse teams often perform better because they combine unique skills and ideas. However, cultural differences can sometimes lead to misunderstandings. To overcome this, communication and open-mindedness are essential. Governments and organizations promote cultural exchange programs to help people experience different ways of life.','B2','2025-09-18 22:59:20.000'),('f6e9a790-94c9-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','B2 – The Future of Renewable Energy','As the world faces the consequences of climate change, renewable energy has become more important than ever. Solar, wind, and hydro power are now widely used to reduce dependence on fossil fuels. Innovations in battery technology make it easier to store and use renewable energy. Although renewable sources are clean, they also face challenges such as high costs and unstable supply. Governments are investing heavily in research to make renewable energy more efficient and affordable for everyone.','B2','2025-09-18 22:59:20.000'),('f81fac2e-949a-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','B2 – Technology and Daily Life','Technology has become an inseparable part of our daily lives. Most people start their mornings by checking messages or news on their smartphones. While technology saves us time and helps us stay connected, it also creates new challenges. For instance, spending too much time online may reduce face-to-face communication. On the other hand, technology allows remote work and online education, which are valuable for modern society. Finding a balance between online and offline life is one of the greatest tasks today.','B2','2025-09-18 17:22:55.719'),('f82a6a1a-949a-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','B2 – The Importance of Travel','Traveling is not only about visiting new places but also about discovering yourself. When you leave your comfort zone, you experience different cultures, food, and traditions. Meeting local people often gives you a better understanding of their way of life than just reading about it. Although traveling can be expensive and tiring, it enriches your perspective. Many people believe that the memories and friendships made during travels are priceless. Therefore, travel is often considered an investment rather than a cost.','B2','2025-09-18 17:22:55.791'),('f82ba31c-949a-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','B2 – Climate Change','Climate change is one of the most serious problems facing humanity. Scientists warn that rising temperatures may cause sea levels to increase and natural disasters to become more frequent. Many governments are trying to reduce carbon emissions, but progress is slow. Individuals also have a role to play: using renewable energy, recycling, and reducing waste can make a difference. Although the problem is global, small actions taken by many people can lead to meaningful change. Future generations will depend on the choices we make today.','B2','2025-09-18 17:22:55.797'),('f82be3e0-949a-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','B2 – Learning Languages','Learning a foreign language can be both exciting and challenging. At the beginning, students often feel nervous about speaking and making mistakes. However, mistakes are an essential part of the process. People who practice regularly usually become more confident and fluent. Moreover, learning another language opens doors to new cultures and career opportunities. In today’s world, where globalization is increasing, being bilingual or multilingual is a valuable skill.','B2','2025-09-18 17:22:55.798'),('f82c00d2-949a-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','B2 – Volunteering','Volunteering means giving your time and effort to help others without expecting money. Many young people choose to volunteer in hospitals, schools, or environmental organizations. They not only help their communities but also gain experience and skills. For example, working with children improves communication, while volunteering in a team develops leadership. Although it requires effort and sacrifice, volunteering often brings personal satisfaction. In fact, many volunteers say they receive more than they give.','B2','2025-09-18 17:22:55.799'),('fe5190e2-949c-11f0-9a3c-3f1fdbf124df','B1 – Morning Exercise','Every morning, Sarah goes jogging in the park. She usually runs for thirty minutes. After jogging, she stretches her muscles and drinks water. Sometimes, she meets friends who join her for a short walk. Regular exercise keeps Sarah healthy and energetic for the day.','B1','2025-09-18 17:37:25.000');
